title: plain cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add egg and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture to margarine mix.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
May sprinkle with crystals or use icing.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; reserve 3 tablespoons liquid.
Flake fish.
In medium bowl, combine salmon and liquid, crumbs, celery, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Form into 5 patties.
In preheated lightly greased skillet over medium heat, fry patties about 3 minutes on each side.
Your choice of toppings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon roasted leg of lamb
directions: Prepare lamb by making inch-deep slices spaced 1-inch apart. In a small saucepan, place vinegar, water, lemon juice, rind, mustard, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and pour over lamb. Bake in a preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently.
When serving, slice thinly and spoon pan juices over meat.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Fold in topping. Pour into crust and freeze.

title: lemon pecan cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, juice and egg.
Blend in dry ingredients and rind.
Chill and roll into balls and flatten on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 6 to 8 minutes until lightly brown on edge.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a jar and refrigerate overnight. Dressing will keep up to 1 week in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, shake dressing well and toss with spinach.
Add bacon, eggs and mushrooms and toss again.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: preacher cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in saucepan on medium heat, boil 3 minutes exactly.
Remove from heat.
Add cocoa, oatmeal, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Beat quickly while hot.
As it thickens, drop quickly by teaspoon on cookie sheet.

title: braised short ribs
directions: Roll short ribs in seasoned flour (about 1 cup flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper). Brown well in large skillet. Put sliced onions in crock-pot; add browned ribs and broth. Cover and cook on low 7 to 10 hours (high 4 to 6 hours). Remove meat to platter and thicken gravy if desired.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add a small amount of oil and milk; mix until smooth.
Dip each wiener into batter; fry until golden brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift spices with flour.
Cream the sugar with butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with applesauce and soda mixture.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute rice in oil until light brown.
Add water, tomato sauce, cumin and garlic.
Dissolve bouillon or broth powder in 1/2 cup of water before adding.
Total amount of liquids should be 4 cups. Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce to a simmer until done, 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: holiday melba dessert
directions: Thaw, crush and strain raspberries; reserve syrup.
Dice and drain peaches, adding enough peach syrup to raspberry to make 1 1/4 cups.
Sprinkle gelatin over syrups and heat, constantly stirring until dissolved.
Beat in cream and mayonnaise; chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in peaches and nuts.
Turn into a 3-cup mold.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Toss in lightly the milk.
Drop by spoonfuls on hot apples.
Bake uncovered for 25 to 35 minutes.
I usually double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil potatoes for 15 minutes; drain. Cook eggs; boil for 10 minutes.
Peel and slice eggs.
Peel and dice onion.
Add potatoes, eggs and onion together.
Add mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on the box.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish with vanilla wafers.
Slice bananas to cover wafers.
Pour half of the pudding mix over the wafers and bananas. Repeat with another layer of wafers, bananas, and pudding.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: In a bowl combine oats, brown sugar, and baking powder.
Add melted butter and eggs.
Fold in nuts or chocolate chips.

title: sacher bars
directions: Melt
butter
and unsweetened chocolate over hot water. Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at
a time, blending well after each addition.
Add flour and vanilla; mix
well.
Spread evenly in greased and floured waxed paper-lined 15
x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until squares spring back when lightly pressed.
Cool
in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Do not overbake.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, vanilla and flour.
Chill, roll out and cut.
Cook at 350° until lightly browned.

title: pecan log
directions: On very low heat, melt margarine, add syrup and marshmallows, a few at a time. Add milk, mix very well. Add pecans, walnuts, raisins, and 1 box crumbs, mix well. This is very thick.

title: hidden valley ranch spicy apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into a serving bowl.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
(Toss apple slices with additional lemon juice to avoid discoloring.)
Makes about 2 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add nuts; stir well. Form a well in center and add eggs, pumpkin and shortening.
Stir well until moist.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel. To drippings, add potatoes, celery, carrots, onion, salt, pepper and water.
Cook, covered, about 15 minutes or until tender.
Combine flour with small amount of milk until smooth. Add to potato mixture along with remaining milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter until fluffy.
Add whipped topping and powdered sugar.
Put into pie crusts.
Freeze 8 hours (overnight).
Shave chocolate over tops of pies and serve.
Makes 2 pies.

title: russian tea
directions: Put tea and cloves in water.
Let come to a boil.
Turn off heat.
Let steep 30 minutes.
In large container (1-gallon), mix undiluted orange juice, pineapple juice, lemon juice, sugar and 2 to 3 quarts water.
Strain tea and add to other ingredients.

title: mountain chow chow(5 gallon recipe)
directions: Chop cabbage very fine. Chop green tomatoes and hot pepper; mix together with cabbage. Pack in a crock jar (stone jar) tightly. Use 5 cups per layer. Sprinkle about 1 tablespoon of canning salt over the first layer. Then add another layer of cabbage mix and canning salt. Pack tightly and continue until the crock jar is full. Place a plate on top of packed cabbage mix. Then place a flint rock on top of the plate and cover with a cloth or a tight cover. Let it "work" for 9 days.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding corn bread mix one box at a time. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Saute onion in butter.
Add Cheez Whiz to broccoli; then add soup and other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: In large bowl stir with fork the flour, sugar and salt. Cut in shortening until crumbly. In small bowl beat together water, vinegar and egg. Add to flour mixture and stir until all ingredients are moistened. Chill 1/2 hour.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice and cream of coconut.
Pour in 7-Up. Spoon in ice cream.
Makes about 3 quarts or 12 servings.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Place chocolate chips, oleo and marshmallows in large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave until all ingredients are melted. Place remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Stir together until all dry ingredients are coated.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and cut up chicken.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of broth.
Cook noodles by directions on package.
Drain.
Mix noodles, chicken, soups, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Pour margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place crushed Ritz crackers on bottom of casserole dish.
Put chopped chicken over crackers.
Mix soups, sour cream and water chestnuts and place on top of chopped chicken.
Cover with
more Ritz crackers and pour 1 stick melted margarine over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Melt butter and mix with crumbs.
Spread half into greased Pyrex dish.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Pour over crumbs.
Pour pie filling over cheese mixture.
Beat Dream Whip and pour on top of cherries.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serves 12.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix well the sugar, dry mustard, salt and grated onion.
Add and mix well the vinegar.
Add slowly while stirring the sunflower oil.
Add poppy seed and mix.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Slowly add scalded milk, stirring all the time. Add vanilla and pour into custard cups or pan and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place in pan of hot water and bake in a 350° oven until knife comes out clean when inserted.
Do not overbake.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend sugar, sweet potato and butter together, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 to 3 pies.

title: fettuccine carbonara with vegetables
directions: In small bowl, beat eggs, Parmesan cheese and pepper. Add carrots and peas during last 2 minutes of cooking noodles.
Place colander over large serving bowl.
Drain pasta and vegetables in the colander to heat bowl.
Pour out the water, then put drained pasta and vegetables.
Immediately pour egg mixture over hot pasta to cook eggs and coat pasta.

title: carrot cream soup
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, melt butter or margarine over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Add carrots and stir in flour, mixing well.
Cook, stirring; add stock and bring to boil, then lower heat.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Put through blender (not too much at a time; will bubble over).
Blend in cream; add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle chopped parsley on top.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Mix, bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Trim all crust from cake, then cut cake into 1-inch cubes.
Put half of cake cubes into inverted seal of Tupperware Fresh and Fancy Cake Taker.
Spread with pie filling.
Add remaining cake cubes in a layer.
Beat cream cheese until softened.
Add milk gradually, beating until smooth.
Fold thawed topping into cheese mixture; spread over cake layer.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes 20 servings.

title: speedy cheesecake pie
directions: Combine crumbs and 3 tablespoons butter.
Press into buttered 8-inch pie plate, building up sides.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Blend in 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and dash of salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Combine dairy sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spoon over top of pie and bake 10 minutes longer.
Cool; chill several hours.
Serve with fresh or frozen fruit if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: christmas salad
directions: Combine apples, drained pineapple and marshmallows. Set aside. Cook the remaining ingredients, include the reserved pineapple juice, until thick. Allow the mixture to cool and pour over fruit. Do not mix. Top with coconut.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and sugar.
Blend well. Add 1 egg (beaten), milk and apples (cut).
Drop by spoonsful into deep hot fat (365°).
Fry for 2 to 5 minutes until golden brown. Drop in powdered sugar or serve with syrup.
Makes about 18.

title: granny's chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain fat. Heat beans, water, ketchup, chili powder and hot sauce. Let simmer while browning meat. Mix together and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish avocado
directions: Combine first four ingredients; set aside.
Combine oil, vinegar, garlic salt and hot sauce; mix.
Reserve 3 tablespoons and pour remaining over tomato.
Line serving dish with lettuce, brush avocados with dressing reserved and serve all on lettuce.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients. Form into ball.
Roll in nuts or sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato wedges
directions: Place potato wedges, cut side down, in pan.
Brush with oil. Sprinkle with salt.
Broil at 550° until brown, about 5 minutes. Turn over, brush with oil and sprinkle with salt.
Broil until tender.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix together Good Seasons, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Put on top of salad. Top with bacon and Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate.
Best to make several hours before serving.
Prior to serving, mix all together. Serves 8.

title: coconut creamed pie
directions: Cook flour, milk and sugar until thick; add egg yolks.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into cooked pie shell; top with meringue.
Bake until brown.

title: franks 'n' sweets
directions: Cut sweet potatoes in half; cut frankfurters in quarters.
Melt butter in small pan; stir in brown sugar and mustard.
Alternate layers of sweet potatoes and frankfurters in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour brown sugar mixture over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbling hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Layer in crock-pot as listed 3 times.
Cook on low 4 to 5 hours.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water, 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Peel and quarter.
Arrange in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: mom's sweet potato roll
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Add shortening, brown sugar, salt and sweet potatoes; cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water. After 5 minutes, stir and combine with cooled milk mixture.
Add 1 cup of the flour and beat until it is smooth; add enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Mix thoroughly.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer pineapple on bottom; add blueberries.
Add sugar on top of blueberries.
Add cake mix.
Cut butter into small pieces and put on top of cake mix.
Top with chopped pecans.

title: picnic cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions; add dry cake mix. Stir well.
Spread
in
a
greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle chocolate	chips
on
top.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Will be gooey.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add milk and dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13 cake pan and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good with chocolate cinnamon icing.
Servings: many.

title: stromboli
directions: Defrost bread dough and place on a greased plate.
Spray or rub oil on dough.
Allow dough to rise.
After dough has risen, mix the egg with oregano, parsley, basil and salt and pepper as desired.
Roll the raised dough into a rectangular shape, about 12 x 18-inch.
Spread the egg mixture on the rolled out dough (save some to put on outside surface).
Put a layer of pepperoni or salami or ham on dough, then a layer of Provolone cheese or cheese of choice.
You may repeat layers of meat or cheese of your choice.
Sprinkle last layer with Parmesan or Romano cheese.
Roll dough as you would a jelly roll.
Press seams and edges to seal. Place seams down on greased cookie sheet.
Baste top of dough with remaining egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until golden brown.

title: cinnamon honey muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat muffin pan with nonstick spray. In a medium bowl combine bran, buttermilk, egg, honey, oil, raisins and carrots.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: mulled cider
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Cook and strain.
Reheat and serve. Add slices of lemon and orange in each cup.
Yields 16 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: lazy chicken
directions: In a 9-inch cake pan, pour rice.
Place chicken pieces on top. Mix water and soup together.
Pour mixture over chicken and rice. Sprinkle onion soup mix over top of chicken.
Place in oven. Cook 2 hours at 350° until chicken is done.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Take peach half, put large marshmallow in center of peach and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Broil until marshmallow is puffed and brown.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in ingredients in order given, except 3 of the olives and cheese. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into baking dish and top with cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Garnish with olives.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ham biscuits(serves 10)
directions: Mix together with electric mixer the butter, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion; spread on rolls. Layer cheese, ham, then cheese. Heat at 350° approximately 15 minutes. May be prepared ahead and frozen.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 15 minutes before serving.

title: low calorie vegetable soup
directions: Cook in small amount of water until tender the carrots, cabbage and onions.
Add tomato juice, tomatoes, green beans, bouillon cubes, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 30 to 45 minutes. Water can be added any time.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: fried lumpia(eggrolls)
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons in each wrapper.
Fry in shortening until golden brown.
Serve hot with sweet and sour sauce or soy sauce.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix together and heat over low flame.
Serve with lamb or beef.

title: cranberry orange nut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in orange juice, egg and orange peel.
Mix only to moisten. Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Spoon into pans, greased and floured.
Bake 60 minutes in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cook on rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool and wrap.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: texas salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in juice of pineapple plus 1 1/2 cups water.
Add lime jello.
Let set in refrigerator until partly congealed.
Remove.
Add pineapple, nuts, cheese and Cool Whip.

title: fat-free fruit smoothies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and mix until smooth. Pour equally into 4 glasses.
Cut a strawberry partially in half (leaving the top intact) and wedge onto side of the glass.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.
Other fruits may be used instead of strawberries.
One cup serving, calories 45, fat 0 and cholesterol 0.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter and flour together until golden brown.
Add bell pepper, green onion and onion to browned mixture; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and two cans of water and salt and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add meat and cook until tender.

title: raw apple salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except apples in medium pot. Cook until thick over medium heat, stirring so it won't stick. Cool completely. Add apples to mixture and spread into a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet and fill with graham crackers.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix next 3 ingredients in pan and boil 2 minutes. Pour over graham crackers and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool and break into quarters.

title: orange sugar cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
In medium bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat 1 sugar, margarine, orange peel and vanilla until creamy.
Add Egg Beaters; beat one minute.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until blended, mix in orange extract.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Shape dough into balls and roll in colored sugar, place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet, press balls with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until light golden brown.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen. 2 grams fat, 60 calories per cookie.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop on baking pan or put into greased muffin pan by spoonful. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: southern sausage casserole
directions: Place croutons in buttered casserole. Top with cheese.
Cook sausage and drain grease.
Put sausage on cheese.
Beat eggs.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour over sausage and cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a 9 x 14-inch casserole.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan or large bowl in microwave.
Add cocoa and stir.
Beat in eggs and sugar.
Fold in flour and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waffle iron at medium temperature.
Bake 1 to 2 minutes, check for doneness with fork. Frost with chocolate frosting or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tomatoes provencales(south of france tomatoes)
directions: Wipe tomatoes and cut in half.
Cook in a little oil in skillet, cut side down, over low heat for 10 minutes.
Transfer to a heatproof serving dish.
Make a paste-like substance with oil, garlic, bread crumbs and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper. Spoon mixture on top of each tomato half.
Bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: night before casserole
directions: Stir together and put in refrigerator, then bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: christmas crispies
directions: Stir the butterscotch pieces and peanut butter in a pan over low heat until the butterscotch melts.
Then pour mixture over the cereal and stir together gently.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Chill for 2 hours or overnight.

title: cherry-vanilla cream cheese whip(low-carb)
directions: Beat until fluffy. Enjoy!

title: tomato green beans
directions: Snap off ends of green beans, then steam them in salted water until done, about 20 minutes.
Heat butter in skillet; stir in basil, lemon pepper and garlic.
Add tomatoes, turning lightly to coat with butter mixture to release a little juice.
Mix beans with tomato mixture and serve.

title: yankee steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; pound into steak.
Brown steak in oil.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; cover with onions. Combine tomato sauce and garlic powder.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: creole corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions; set aside. Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine until tender. Remove from heat; add corn, rice, eggs, pimientos, 1 cup of the Cheddar cheese and Creole seasoning to taste. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle balance of cheese on top and melt. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: salmon corn chowder
directions: In a medium saucepan heat butter until melted.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 5 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Stir in milk, tomatoes, salmon, corn, dill, salt and black pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add Monterey Jack cheese, stirring until melted.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water until set. Combine cream cheese and vanilla together.
Add to jello.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread cheese mixture over crust.
Refrigerate until served.

title: broccoli lasagne
directions: Place broccoli boxes on paper towel.
Microwave on High (9 minutes), turning once.
Drain and squeeze out moisture.
Discard liquid.
In a 1-quart mixing bowl, microwave margarine for 1 minute on High.
Whisk in flour until smooth and onion powder; whisk in milk.
Microwave on High 6 minutes, whisking midway.
Whisk and add Cheddar cheese until melted.
Blend in broccoli.
Set aside.

title: banana nut cake
directions: In large bowl, sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add bananas; beat 2 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: christmas pretzel salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip. Spread over pretzels. Drain (save juice) from pineapple and strawberries (drain and save juice also). Take liquid off pineapple and strawberries. Add enough water to make 3 cups. Bring to boil. Add jello. Dissolve. Throw in fruit. Put in fridge until set. Pour over cream cheese mixture.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: Dredge pork chops with flour.
Brown chops in oil.
Place on each chop, 1 tablespoon rice, 1 slice of tomato and 1 slice of onion.
Place in covered pan.
Slowly add boiling water.
Cover and place in oven.
Cook at 375° for 40 minutes or until tender.
A tasty one dish meal when accompanied by your favorite salad.

title: cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese; fold in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with mandarin oranges, if desired.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar together.
Mix eggs and melted butter together.
Then mix all ingredients together, except rhubarb.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle rhubarb over the top.
Bake at 350° in center of oven until brown.
Insert knife in center.
If knife comes out clean, it's ready.
Pie is done approximately 45 to 55 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim steak; wipe with a damp paper towel.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Pound into steak on both sides.
Brown meat.
Place vegetables and tomato sauce on meat.
Simmer slowly about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Layer sliced cabbage, onion, grated cheese and salt and pepper to taste in ovenproof dish.
Cover top with can of soup.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Break cauliflower into medium size flowerets. Cook in boiling water until crisp-tender. Drain well and set aside.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together after sifting flour.
Mix other ingredients in.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight before baking. Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Batter can be kept in refrigerator for one month.
If you use applesauce and egg substitute fat grams are less than 2 per muffin.
Very good and so convenient to have in the refrigerator to bake.

title: ed mcmahon's leg of lamb
directions: Make 5 slits in top of lamb and insert 1 clove of garlic in each.
Mark with a toothpick for easy removal.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with Dijon mustard and sprinkle with parsley. Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, then baste with Burgundy.
Bake about 1/2 hour longer.
When done, remove from liquid.
Skim off grease and use pan juices to spoon over lamb if desired.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Add marshmallows to milk.
Heat over boiling water until melted.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix.
Cool until cold.
Fold in whipped cream, chocolate and nuts.
Pour into graham pie crust. Sprinkle on toasted coconut.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine flour, salt, mustard and pepper; stir in milk until smooth.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. When hot, add margarine and cheese; stir.
When cheese is melted, add macaroni.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes until bubbly.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and cocoa.
Add 1/2 milk (1 cup) and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat until it begins to thicken; add rest of milk and cook until thick.
Add 1/2 cup butter.
Pour into cooked pie crust and top with meringue made of 3 egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: bohemian cake
directions: Sift flour and mix with spices and salt.
Set aside.
Cream sugars, eggs and oil.
Beat buttermilk and soda by hand.
Add to creamed mixture.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Mix and bake in layers or tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt yeast in water.
Put flour, egg, sugar, salt, shortening and yeast mix in bowl.
Mix well and let raise for 30 minutes. Roll the dough round shaped.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar, butter and nuts.
Roll up and slice 1-inch thick.
Place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Let raise again to double size.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frenchies toasties
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Dip the bread into the mixture, one at a time.
In a large frying pan, place 2 teaspoons Puritan oil.
Heat and add the dipped bread. Fry until golden brown on each side on a medium heat.

Place all the slices in the pan, on low heat and cover for about 3 minutes. This will plump up the slices. Serve with whipped cream or canned pie filling, jelly, powdered sugar or syrup. Ice cream can also be used.
These can be frozen and reheated in microwave at a later date if left over.
Makes 8 to 10 slices.

title: mama's banana pudding
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Add the already blended ingredients until
it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Pour in layers in a bowl alternating
with
layers of vanilla wavers and sliced bananas.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until tender; save broth.
Saute bell pepper and pimentos in broth.
Add cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix with chicken, cut in small pieces.
Heat together.
Cut tortilla shells in two and place in casserole dish. Layer shells, chicken and soup mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Heat in oven at 350°.

title: brown bag apple pie(no muss, no fuss)
directions: Put apples in bowl.
Mix with sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Place apple mixture into pie shell.
Pat apples down evenly.

title: salmon pie
directions: Flake salmon and remove large bones.
Cook potatoes and mash with milk.
Mix all ingredients with onion, salt and pepper.
Put into an 8-inch 2-crust pie.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until crust is brown on bottom.
Can be served with white sauce and peas.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix everything but macaroni and pour this over drained macaroni. Mix. Chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and pull off bone.
Put in bottom of baking dish. Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Mix milk with flour and baking powder.
Mix together until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix chicken broth and cream of celery soup and heat.
Pour over the milk and flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cukes and remove ends.
Cut into thin slices.
Put into nonmetal bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and add cold water.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: broiled shrimp wrapped in bacon
directions: Soak 8 bamboo skewers in water to cover for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, cook bacon in a wide frying pan over medium heat until some of the fat has cooked out and bacon begins to brown (bacon should not be crisp).
Drain and then cut each slice in half, lengthwise.
Wrap one bacon half slice around each shrimp.

title: schnitzel pork
directions: Pound the pork loins until they are thin.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll pork loins in flour until coated good on both sides. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain and serve.
Serves 3 to 6.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add fruit cocktail and eggs. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, pecans and coconut.
Spread over top of batter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell peppers in margarine until tender.
Add chopped gizzards.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan acccording to package directions.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Mix instant pie filling as directed.
Set aside.
Using large punch bowl begin layering with layer of cake squares; top with cherry pie filling, whipped topping, pineapple, instant vanilla pie filling, nuts and cherries.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: cookie tree ornaments
directions: Mix baking soda, cornstarch and water in saucepan. Cook on medium-high heat. The mixture will form a ball similar to pie dough.
Let cool a few minutes. Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Use cookie cutters to cut out shapes.
Make small hole in each one with toothpick or skewer.
Let dry overnight on baking sheet. Do not cook.
Paint.
Add ribbon or string for hanging.
(Try adding food coloring to dough before rolling for different effects.)

title: texas bon bon
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except chocolate in a large bowl. Make into small balls (about the size of a walnut).

title: nut bread
directions: Pour into buttered bread pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pot roast
directions: Pat flour over roast and brown in oil.
Place roast in large pot with lid.
Combine onion soup, mushroom soup and 2 cups of water.
Pour over roast.
Cook several hours until tender. Thicken the soup for gravy before serving.
Add carrots and potatoes last hour of cooking.

title: spinach pesto with pasta
directions: Puree first 9 ingredients in blender or food processor until smooth; set aside.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Stir in cheese, mustard and red pepper.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth. Knead just until smooth.
Roll dough out about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Bring a small amount of salted water to a boil.
Add broccoli.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix broccoli, cheese, onion and green pepper; put in a greased pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients well.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: mom's bread balls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, add ingredients.
Mix well by hand. Drop by tablespoon in cooking oil.
Fry until golden brown over medium heat.

title: spicy zucchini fritters
directions: Cut zucchini into finger size pieces.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Allow batter to rest refrigerated for 12 hours. Fold in stiff egg whites.
Dip zucchini into batter and deep fry.

title: mom raymond's quick salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Add Cool Whip; mix. Refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: braided egg bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening, and 4 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth. Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board, knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turn greased side up. Cover, let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: english pea salad
directions: Slice the 4 vegetables.
Blend all ingredients with Miracle Whip. Add pepper and paprika to taste.

title: oil dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together in blender.
Blend well and until thick.
Refrigerate.
Makes 5 cups.

title: peggy's beef spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, horseradish, Parmesan cheese and chipped beef all together.
Spread on Wheat Thins or Ritz crackers.

title: sock-it-to-me-cake
directions: Mix ingredients and cook at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix together all ingredients except eggs.
Add eggs; stir until well blended.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done. Insert tip of knife blade in pudding about halfway between edge and center of pie.
Should come out clean.

title: lydia's easy chicken casserole
directions: Lay chicken in bottom of greased glass baking dish.
Combine soup and water and pour over chicken.
Mix Stove Top stuffing according to package directions and spread over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into a buttered casserole dish.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions and pour over coconut and pecans.

title: chicken curry
directions: Wash and drain chicken in colander.
Place the oil in a large cooking pot, preferably a heavy cast aluminium pot.
Peel and thinly slice the onions and garlic and place them in the oil that has been pre-heated at medium-high heat.
Cook these until golden brown, stirring occasionally.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add softened cream cheese.
Beat again until smooth.
Turn into crumb crust.
Refrigerate approximately 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping or drizzle with chocolate ice cream topping or raspberry preserves.
Ten minutes to make.
Three hours to chill.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: pecan fudge pie
directions: Combine chocolate crumbs and 1/3 cup of melted butter; firmly press mixture on bottom and sides of a 9-inch tart pan or pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressing and cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve with fresh ground black pepper, if desired.

title: five flavor pound cake with glaze
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed about 2 minutes or until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed just until blended after each addition. Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and place on wire rack.
Spoon glaze over cake while warm.

title: fish fillets with lemon thyme
directions: Microwave fillets in serving dish with lemon thyme on top for 4 minutes.
During this time, mix crumbs, cheese and oleo. Preheat oven to 350°.
Add more thyme to fillets after you turn them. Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using only stick margarine.
Mix remaining 1/2 stick margarine with cornflakes.
Sprinkle on top. Bake in 9 x 13-inch oblong pan for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: yam balls
directions: Cook, drain and mash sweet potatoes.
Add sugar and crushed pineapple which has been drained.
Get large marshmallows and cover with the potato mixture.
Roll them in coconut and place in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes until coconut is toasted and the marshmallows burst open.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, Eagle Brand Milk, gradually.
Add peanut butter, mix well.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour in two Chocolate Crumb Crust.

title: the bomber plant cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients. Add eggs, vanilla, baking soda, flour, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix and pour on greased sheet pan. Cook 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Dissolve sugar in liquid with eggs.
Add dry ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 3 small loaves or 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan makes 2 loaves.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast to dry mixture.
Mix well; add more flour as needed.
Roll out to 2/3-inch and cut with small biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Dough can be placed in refrigerator, covered, and used as needed or can freeze biscuits and use as needed.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Note:
Add more flour (up to 1/2 cup) if batter is too thin.

title: belgian pate
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in crock or covered bowl in refrigerator.
Best if refrigerated overnight before serving. Serve with party rye bread.

title: southern pralines(in microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, milk and salt in a 2-quart measuring cup (glass); mix well.
Stir in butter.
Microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes or until mixture reaches soft ball stage (235°), stirring once.
Stir in pecans and cool about 1 minute.
Beat by hand until mixture is creamy and begins to thicken, about 3 minutes.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on box.
Line a pie plate or cake pan bottom with vanilla wafers.
Open pineapple and drain all juice off.
When pudding is done, remove from heat and add pineapple.
Mix well and pour onto vanilla wafers.
Chill until thickened, then serve.

title: shawn's hawaiian fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients until all mixed very well.

title: pickled corn
directions: When the corn becomes roasting ears, boil the corn-on-the-cob and pack in a churn on the cob or if you prefer, cut the corn from the cob, sprinkling a thin layer of salt alternately with the corn. When the corn is pickled, it can be eaten directly from the cob or if you prefer it cut off, fry in bacon grease or butter.
The corn keeps well.

title: natillas(dessert)
directions: In
blender put about 1/2 cup milk, egg yolks and flour for a
few
minutes;
set
aside.
Put
sugar
in
saucepan, caramelized until light brown.
Add remaining milk to bring to boil;
sugar will dissolve.
Simmer about 5 minutes, stirring. Beat the egg whites until stand in peak.
Put them by spoonful on top of natillas; add cinnamon.

title: oatmeal shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350 for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately cut into bars.
Cool completely.
Remove carefully.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix 1 cup pecans, flour and butter; press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until light brown.
Beat together 10x sugar and cream cheese until fluffy. Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk and spread on top of second layer.
Top with whipped topping and pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: matzo meal latkes(pancakes)
directions: Separate eggs (yolks and whites).
Beat whites until stiff. Beat yolks and add other ingredients.
Add whites (fold in).
Drop by spoonful on greased frypan.
Brown both sides.
Serve with cinnamon and sugar or jelly.

title: beer bread
directions: In mixing bowl briefly mix flour, beer and sugar.
Transfer to greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes more until toothpick in center comes out clean.

title: brisket
directions: Season brisket with salt, pepper and small amount of garlic powder.
Make strong cup of coffee.
Put brisket in foil; pour coffee over brisket.
Seal foil and cook at 200° for 24 hours (yes, 24 hours).

title: mushrooms magnifico(appetizer)
directions: Wipe mushrooms; clean and remove stems.
Stuff caps with herbed cream cheese.
To make cheese, soften the cream cheese and add all remaining ingredients except wine, butter and Mozzarella.
Melt butter in ovenproof skillet and add mushrooms (stuffed side up). Saute about 2 minutes over medium heat.
Add a bit of wine or water to cover bottom of skillet.
Top the mushrooms with the Mozzarella. Place in heated oven at 350° until cheese melts (about 5 to 10 minutes).
Place on serving dish with pan juices poured over. Serve warm.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Mix and
boil
8 minutes the powdered sugar, evaporated milk, chocolate
chips and 1/2 cup margarine.
Add vanilla and set aside and
cool.
Crush
cookies
and
add 1/2 cup melted margarine. Put
Hydrox mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze. Spread 1
1/2 cups
peanuts
over Hydrox mixture.
Spread ice cream over peanuts.
Chill until firm, then cover with chocolate mixture and freeze.

title: mag crump's shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in baked pie shell.
Combine in saucepan water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir until comes to boil.
Continue cooking on low about 2 minutes or until clear and thick.
Add jello, stir until dissolved. Pour over berries while still hot.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken angelo
directions: Dip chicken in eggs, coat with bread crumbs.
Saute until brown.
Transfer to 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange half the mushrooms over it.
Cover with sliced cheese and top with remaining mushrooms.
Pour chicken broth over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crazy cake(chocolate, eggless cake)
directions: Mix slightly. Add 1 cup water and mix until batter is smooth. Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan (double batch use a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan) at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until top springs back when pressed.

title: blueberries in the snow
directions: Bake angel food cake as per directions.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Mix Dream Whip and add to mixture.
But reserve enough Dream Whip to put on top of cake. Mixture goes between layers and around sides.
Keep refrigerated.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine beans, onion, mustard, brown sugar, catsup and bacon in baking dish.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spice apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Cook at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: *May combine 1/2 teaspoon prepared horseradish and 1/2 teaspoon Dijon mustard to make horseradish mustard.

title: hot turkey casserole
directions: Make dressing from broth.
Put 1-inch layer in bottom of large baking dish.
Combine turkey, vegetables, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Spread this over dressing.
Combine beaten eggs and milk.
Pour over casserole and chill for 1 hour.
Spoon mushroom soup over casserole as it comes from can.
Bake in slow oven at 325° until done (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Spread cheese on top; put under broiler to melt.

title: spiced coffee mix
directions: Combine coffee, sugar and spices in blender container. Process for 30 seconds. Store in airtight container.
Yields 1 cup.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Add all of the ingredients and mix together.
Pour peaches on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until cake is done.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Melt chocolate bits and margarine in a saucepan.
Cool.
When it is cool enough so as not to melt marshmallows, add marshmallows and mix until well coated.
Tear 2 pieces of wax paper 20 inches long.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut along the length of the paper. Pour 1/2 mixture over the coconut and 1/2 cup coconut on the top. Shape into a log, roll in wax paper.
This makes 2 logs.
Chill for 14 hours, then slice.

title: grits casserole
directions: Let water come to a boil.
Sprinkle grits into the water.
Let cook until almost done.
Mix garlic, cheese, butter and milk with grits.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: gazpacho(cold tomato soup)
directions: Puree canned tomatoes in blender.
To peel whole, fresh tomatoes, drop whole tomatoes in boiling water for 15 to 20 seconds, then chop.
Add all ingredients together in a large bowl with the vinegar (start with 3 tablespoons); add more vinegar, only if you want the soup to be more tart.

title: cereal mix
directions: Melt butter and spices together.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bag and pour into roasting pan.
Pour liquid over mixture until coated, but not soggy.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: surprise cookies
directions: Blend together margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add the flour and chopped nuts; beat on low speed until blended thoroughly.
Chill dough in refrigerator for 1 hour. Roll a small piece of dough about the size of a walnut around a kiss.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar after cooled.

title: fried apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour large flat pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Blend apples with sugar, oil,
eggs (well beaten), nuts and vanilla.
Add flour mixed with soda, cinnamon and salt.
Bake very slowly for 1 hour.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or plain.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Chop candied cherries and pineapple.
Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually add 1 cup flour, mixing well.
In a separate bowl thoroughly mix pineapple, cherries, raisins and pecans in remaining flour.
Pour cream mixture over fruit and nut mixture.
Mix well. Put in pan and place in a 300° oven, not preheated, for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 250° and bake 2 hours and 30 minutes longer.
Makes a 5 pound cake.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together, then add 1/2 of Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Chill several hours.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar in a small mixing bowl until smooth and creamy.
Add flour and walnuts; mix to make a crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remainder into bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: chocolate yum yum cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets, spacing about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 minutes.
While still warm; place chocolate rectangle on top of each cookie.
Gently spread.
Sprinkle with candy sprinkles.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Place chicken pieces in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan or dish.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Uncover and bake 45 additional minutes, basting occasionally.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until done.
Makes 8 dozen, depending on size you make them.

title: sugar-free punch
directions: Wire whisk 2 to 3 cups lemon-lime beverage with dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and chill.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables, celery and onion until tender; drain. Combine vegetables with 1/2 stick margarine, cheese and mayonnaise.
Put in baking dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix all ingredients, one at a time.
Put in casserole, uncovered, and bake at 350° for 25 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Prepare meat with tenderizer according to label directions. Place in Dutch oven.
Pour mixture of remaining ingredients over roast.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours or until tender.
Make gravy from pan drippings.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In large bowl, combine sour cream and cream cheese; stir until smooth.
On a large platter, spread mixture to a circle.
Spread taco sauce evenly on top of cheese mixture.
Layer with lettuce, green pepper, onion, Cheddar cheese and Monterey Jack cheese over the taco sauce.
Sprinkle tomato over all.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill and make into rolls on wax paper. Freeze.
When ready to cook, slice and bake at 375 ° for 10 to 12 minutes, until brown around edges.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 24 muffin tin cups.
Mix egg, milk, honey and melted butter or margarine together.
Mash the bananas with a fork and add to mixture.
Mix flour, oatmeal, nuts, baking powder, soda and salt together. Add to banana mixture. Stir until just moistened.
Do not beat. Fill muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tested with a toothpick. Remove from pan. Cool. Serve warm or cold.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Prepare pizza crust as directed on box. Spread on lightly greased pizza pan, add sausage, then pour beaten eggs over sausage. Crumble hash brown first then cheese over top of pizza and bake. Bake at 350 degree for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon fillet with dill
directions: In a small saucepan, saute crushed garlic in olive oil very briefly.
Add lemon juice and stir. Pour over fish.
Sprinkle with dill.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes depending on thickness of salmon.
Serve over rice with steamed broccoli and salad. Serves 3.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let set until almost firm. Whip with softened cream cheese.
Whip chilled Pet milk until soft pearls form.
Add sugar.
Whip the two mixtures together and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring with a fork only until combined.
Drop dough from tablespoon directly in bubbly chicken or beef broth.
Return to boiling.
Cover tightly. Reduce heat.
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes.

title: graham cracker brittle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and sugar together.
Lay graham crackers (broken into fourths) on a large cookie sheet with sides.
Arrange broken pecans on top of crackers.
Spoon melted margarine over all.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Watch closely!

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer ingredients in order listed in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm or cool with whip cream or ice cream.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a hard, rolling boil.
Cook rapidly for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly (scorches easily).
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: the easiest cookies even a kid could make
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Preheat oven to 350°. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
May garnish before baking or leave plain.

title: husband's delight pie
directions: Melt butter.
Pour flour and pecans into small cake pan.
Pour melted butter over. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Chill.

title: stratta
directions: Line pan (grease with butter) with 12 slices bread, 6 slices for bottom and 6 for top.
Layer Cheddar cheese, chopped broccoli and diced ham.

title: reuben sandwich hors d'oeuvre
directions: Chop corned beef.
Drain sauerkraut.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 325°. Serve with rye bread.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop 1 cup unpopped popcorn.
In saucepan, melt margarine, brown sugar, light corn syrup and salt.
Boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly, while at rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and vanilla, mixing well.
Put popped popcorn into brown grocery bag.
Pour in caramel mixture and stir well.
Fold over end of bag and place in microwave.
Microwave for 1 minute on High power (100%).
Remove bag and shake it vigorously.
Repeat this 2 more times.
Pour onto cookie sheet and break apart when cooler. Store in plastic container.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Add tomato sauce, garlic salt and oregano to taste. Mix cottage cheese and eggs. Layer beef mixture, noodles, beef mixture, egg, Mozzarella cheese, noodles, beef mixture, egg, Mozzarella cheese and beef mixture. Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine; add onion and cook until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well blended.
Gradually stir in broth, then add garlic and broccoli which has been cut into small pieces.
You may need to add water.
Cook until broccoli is tender; stir in half and half and heat stirring constantly. Remove from heat and either puree with hand mixer or in blender. Return to pan and heat thoroughly.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, peanut butter, vanilla, sugar & butter until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Gently spoon into crust. Garnish with chocolate or cookie crumbs.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours on medium heat.
This is great for freezing.

title: candy bar fudge
directions: Heat butter, cocoa, brown sugar and milk in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla. Pour into greased 8 inch square pan.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop in hot grease.
Cook until golden brown.

title: lite and fluffy salad
directions: Let Cool Whip thaw slightly.
Blend Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Slowly add Jell-O and stir until well mixed.
Add fruit and pecans if you want to and stir.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix the sugar and flour together.
Add lemon juice and rind, slightly beaten egg yolks, butter and salt.
Stir in the milk and mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into first mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake as directed. Cool. Crumble 1/2 cake in large bowl. Put one-half pudding over cake.
Add 1 can cherry pie filling. Put 1/2 Cool Whip over cherries. Repeat next layer. Place cherries on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Add mayonnaise, cream of celery soup and Velveeta cheese.
Mix together.
On top of this, put crackers and margarine.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Squeeze dry.
Mix together all ingredients except bread.
Refrigerate.
Cut center out of Hawaiian bread and cut into squares.
Place dip inside.
Use bread and vegetables.

title: tuna salad
directions: Prepare rice as described on package.
Drain, if necessary. Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown beef.
Add pepper, celery and onion until slightly cooked.
Add one tablespoon sugar, mustard, vinegar, salt, catsup and ground spice.
Cook very slowly in skillet for at least 1 hour.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift sugar and plain flour and set aside.
Combine butter or margarine, Coca-Cola, cooking oil, cocoa and marshmallows in small saucepan and heat until mixed well.
Then add to flour and sugar mixture.
Then add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: In a big bowl sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and
salt.	Make
a
well in the center and add butter, milk and vanilla.
Beat
for
minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after
each
addition.
Then add cream and beat in.
Bake	at 325°
for
1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water; cook slowly, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft-ball stage (236°).
Add peanuts and salt.
Cook to hard-crack stage (295°).
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and soda; stir slightly.
Pour evenly into well-greased shallow pans.
Cool partially by lifting around edges with knife.
When firm, turn. When cold, break in pieces.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen pieces.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Place pecans over the bottom of a greased cake pan. Place coconut on top of pecans.
Mix German chocolate cake to directions and put on top of the coconut and pecans.
Mix the margarine, cream cheese, and powdered sugar together and spread very carefully on top of cake mix (DO NOT STIR).
Place in 350 degree oven and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
No frosting needed.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix sugar
with
cranberries;
let
stand.
Mix
flour, baking powder,
soda and salt and sift.
Beat together orange juice, rind, egg and oil.
Stir this into dry mixture, mixing just
to dampen.
Carefully fold in chopped nuts, cranberries and
sugar. Spoon
batter
into well greased, wax paper lined loaf
pan
and let stand 20 minutes before baking in 350° oven for about 1 hour. Test with toothpick.

title: chicken san souci
directions: Cook the chicken breast with celery tops and salt in water until done.
Drain, remove from bone and set aside.
Cook the wild rice according to package directions.
Saute the onion in butter; remove from the skillet.
Add more butter (I use a stick) and blend in the flour.
Stir in the soup, which has been mixed with the milk.
Add salt, pepper, mushrooms and sauteed onion; set aside.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Add milk if thick.

title: festive potatoes
directions: Pare and cook potatoes in water until tender (30 to 40 minutes).
Drain, mash and beat in cream cheese, sour cream and garlic salt until light and fluffy.
Spoon into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter, sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be made ahead and refrigerated. Allow an extra half hour baking time.

title: oven baked scrambled eggs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) baking dish.
In large bowl combine eggs, milk, butter, salt, pepper and nutmeg; beat well.

Stir in frozen vegetables, 1 cup of the cheese and onions; mix well. Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes; or until eggs are just set in center, stirring twice during baking.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted. Yields 12 servings.
tags: Green Giant American Mixtures California style frozen cauliflower

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Measure all dry ingredients, mix and add to eggs.
Beat well and add pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: spoon cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Using a large spoon as your measure, into a medium mixing bowl put cornmeal, flour and sugar, blending together.
In small bowl, whisk eggs together and pour in.
Add 3/4 cup buttermilk.
In a loaf pan or 9-inch cake pan, pour oil and swirl until pan bottom and sides are covered.
Pour the remaining oil into the bowl with the other ingredients.
Toss.
Add more buttermilk until smooth pouring consistency is reached.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding(aunt alma's)
directions: Combine ingredients in the order listed and bake.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish and refrigerate until set enough to spread sour cream over mixture.
Then gently spread the balance of strawberry mixture over sour cream and refrigerate for about 2 hours before serving or longer.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Melt margarine over low heat in a 2-quart
saucepan.	Remove	from heat.
Stir in sugar, then stir in	egg.
Then
stir in flour, salt, vanilla and pecans. Spread in	well-greased
(with margarine) square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Bake
for
minutes.
Do
not overbake.	Cut into bars after it has cooled.

title: sausage pies
directions: Allow sausage to cool.
Grate cheese.
Combine flour, cheese and dry ingredients; spread over pie shell.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.
Serve.

title: terry's special secret sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use as marinade for pork, beef or chicken

title: cereal nut cookies
directions: Beat together butter, egg, sugar, brown sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix together flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar; mix with butter mixture until well mixed.
Stir in oatmeal, Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Roll in balls and flatten with glass with sugar on the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: '32 ford polka dot cake
directions: Mix chopped dates and hot water; set aside to cool.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with date mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Spread batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with rest of chocolate chips and the nuts.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 35 minutes.

title: boiled potatoes with noodles
directions: Peel and chunk potatoes.
Fry and crumble bacon.
Saute onion in bacon grease.
In a large cooking pot, cover 2-inches above potatoes with water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Boil for about 15 minutes or until almost done. Add noodles. Cook until done. (Drain, if necessary.)
Add bacon, onion with grease, salt and pepper to taste.
Toss.
Serve hot.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into oblong cake pan or baking dish.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread into even layer.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer; spread evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Put slices of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.
Can be served with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and oatmeal.
Add nuts and coconut, if desired.
Beat mixture until it starts to get stiff.
Drop teaspoon size drops on wax paper.
Cool.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: deep-fried walnut chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces; sprinkle with sherry, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy.
Gradually add cornstarch to egg whites, beating until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold in chicken.
Roll each chicken piece in chopped walnuts; fry in 2 inches hot oil (350°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve chicken with Gingered Plum
Sauce.
Yield:
about 3 dozen appetizers.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put ingredients in blender for 30 seconds.
Grease and flour 9 or 10-inch deep pie dish.
Top with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Combine sugar, water and apples in a microwave-safe bowl. Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in cinnamon candy.
Cook on High for 7 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: round steak
directions: Place round steak in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Pour mushroom soup over steak; salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until steak is tender.

title: peas and corn medley
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and cook 30 to 35 minutes or until peas are tender.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat juice in a saucepan.
Add the apple slices.
Stir in cornstarch which has been blended with a little water.
Pour into a 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Dot with margarine and put on the top crust.
Bake as usual (400° for 10 minutes, then 350° until browned).
Do not use tart apples.

title: fruited chicken breast
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half lengthwise.
Sprinkle with salt. Arrange chicken in a baking dish.
Dissolve bouillon in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Stir in orange peel, orange juice, green onions and dash of pepper.
Pour over chicken; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Remove chicken from dish and place on platter. Strain dish juices and reserve 3/4 cup for sauce.
In saucepan, blend cornstarch with 2 tablespoons cold water.
Stir in reserved juices; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and bubbly.
One-half cup grapes can be added to sauce for extra flavor.
Spoon sauce over chicken and sprinkle with paprika.

title: hush puppies
directions: Make into rolls and cook in hot oil.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sour cream to creamed mixture, along with soda and extracts.
Add eggs, two at a time, with 1 cup of flour, until all eggs and flour have been added.
Beat well after each addition.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in 10-inch pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs together.
Add other ingredients. Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Make pie crust according to directions and add pecans before rolling out.

title: fruited cottage cheese salad
directions: Blend cottage cheese with Cool Whip.
Stir in dry jello.
Fold in drained pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Needs to be chilled in refrigerator overnight.
Makes a large salad.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and salt to soft ball stage.
Add marshmallows and peanut butter before removing from fire.
Do not stir.
Cool to room temperature.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy and thick and will hold it's shape when dropped from teaspoon.
Drop into shallow, buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: rice and vegetable casserole
directions: Stir-fry tomatoes, onion, celery, corn, garlic, thyme, savory, chicken seasoning and salt.
Add after sauteed, tomato paste, water, yeast flakes and McKay's seasoning.
Cook 5 minutes.
Place 3 cups of rice evenly in a sprayed casserole dish and spread the sauteed vegetables over the rice.
Cover with remaining rice. Grate millet and Cashew Cheese and sprinkle evenly over the top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit smoothy
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
If using fresh fruit, add 2 cups of ice to the blender.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce. Spread approximately 1/2-inch thick on serving dish.
Top with cocktail sauce.
Put shredded crab meat on top of sauce and garnish with chopped parsley.
Serve with Sociables crackers or Wheat Thins.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Used canned fruit.
Suggestions for fruit are fruit cocktail, pineapple chunks, maraschino cherries and sliced peaches.
Drain the fruit well.
When drained, put 1 cup of sugar for each cup of fruit in a large, glass container.
Stir gently to dissolve. Leave the fruit at room temperature, covered.
The fruit will begin to get the "brandied" taste in about a week.
The longer it sits, the better it gets.

title: 8 layer dip
directions: On a 12 to 14-inch serving plate, spread bean dip to about 3/8-inch thickness.
Carefully spread avocado dip on bean dip to within 3/4-inch of edges.
Spoon sour cream on avocado dip to within 3/4-inch of previous edge.
Top with remaining ingredients arranged in concentric circles.
Cover; chill.
Serve with crackers or corn chips.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and peppers in oil.
Add chicken and mixed vegetables.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni, following directions on box in step one, then pour into pan with sauteed vegetables and 3 cups of hot water.
Cook until tender (approximately 15 minutes).

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, mix 1/4 cup of soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape into 6 firm patties.
In skillet over medium-high heat, cook patties a few at a time, until browned on both sides. Spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and mushroom sauce; return patties to skillet.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until done, turning patties occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour and soda to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk and vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in 3 pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: meat and rice dish
directions: Cook rice until done. While cooking rice, brown hamburger and onion; drain. Add cheese, tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer until cheese melts. In baking dish, combine rice, sauce and water, then add bacon on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molded fruit salad
directions: Combine yogurt with lemon juice and salt; blend well.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Soften gelatin in the pineapple juice and heat until dissolved.
Stir into yogurt mixture.
Add berries. Beat with mixer.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir in pineapple and peaches.
Pour into one quart mold and chill until set.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.

title: spinach salad
directions: Glazed Almonds: In small pan, melt 2 tablespoons sugar and fry almonds over medium-high heat until dark golden brown. Pour them on a plate to cool and harden.

title: basic recipe for cream pies
directions: Coconut Pie:
Add 1 cup coconut to filling; sprinkle a little coconut on meringue.

title: terrah's favorite strawberry pie
directions: Fill pie crust with sliced strawberries.
Mix water, sugar and cornstarch in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Cool for 5 minutes and pour over strawberries.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and Crisco.
Add both sugars and eggs; beat well.
Add flour, cream of tartar and soda; stir well.
Add vanilla.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Press with glass bottom, dipped in sugar, after placing on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tuna fish pie with cheese rolls
directions: Melt butter and add green peppers and onion.
Cook until soft. Add flour.
Stir until well blended.
Add salt.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into large baking dish and cover with cheese rolls.
Serves 8.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package.
As soon as cake comes from oven, punch holes in top of cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut over cake; let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over top. Sprinkle coconut over this.
Refrigerate overnight before cutting.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; add mayonnaise to taste. Garnish with lettuce and parsley.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake for 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: play dough(not edible)
directions: Combine.
Cook 3 minutes.
Dump out and knead.
Store in a covered container at room temperature.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Chop green onions and ham.
Combine all ingredients together.
Form into ball.
Chill and serve.

title: wild horse mountain barbecued beans
directions: Fry bacon over medium heat; drain and crumble into small pieces. Brown ground beef and sausage; drain and add to bacon. Drain canned beans of excess liquid and combine them with meat mixture. Stir in molasses, brown sugar, mustard, ginger, cayenne pepper, cumin, garlic, course pepper, and barbecue sauce. Mix in 6 qt. crockpot and cook approximately 4 to 6 hours.

title: chili and cheese dip
directions: Heat hot dog sauce in saucepan until hot.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Pour into bowl and use as a dip with tortilla chips.

title: pork chops-n-rice
directions: Coat pan with olive oil.
Add pork chops, bell pepper, onion and rice; then pour V-8 all over.
Cook at medium heat for 1 hour and 30 minutes, then simmer until desired consistency (you may need water).

title: as good as casa ole cheese dip
directions: Saute onion with butter.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes with juice.
Add cheeses.
Stir.
Heat until fluffy and melted.
Stir often.

title: southwestern tuna
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix mayo, mustard and lemon juice together; pour over drained tuna.
Mix together well and add rest of ingredients. Stir together.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: easy chicken and noodles
directions: Place chicken, broth and seasoning in saucepan. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes. Add soup and simmer 10 minutes. Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain well and add margarine. Add chicken mixture to noodles in a large pan and heat thoroughly. Easy and delicious!

title: apple enchiladas
directions: Mix pecans in with apple filling.

title: frozen strawberry squares
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine flour, brown sugar and nuts;
pour
over
melted
butter and spread in pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Save 1/2 cup of crumbs for topping.

title: carrot-potato soup
directions: Place potatoes, carrots, leek and chicken stock in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; simmer 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Puree vegetables and liquid a little at a time until smooth.
Put back into saucepan.
Add pepper, salt and cream.
Mix well.
Heat for 10 minutes.
Serve warm or chill for 6 hours and serve cold.
Serves 8.

title: 2 + 2 + 2 pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour. Add extract.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake in tube pan or loaf pans.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients. Put in shallow baking dish.
Cover with flakes or crumbs.
Pour 1/2 cup butter over top.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy chicken and dumplins
directions: Stew chicken until tender; pick chicken off bone.
Mix chicken with broth from the stewing.
Add cream of chicken soup with skim milk, salt and pepper.
Bring to rapid boil.
Add dumplins: Bisquick drop biscuit recipe on side of Bisquick box.
Drop dumplins in boiling chicken mixture.
Boil until done.

title: pizza mix hors d'oeuvres or sandwich
directions: Grind up cheese, chillies, butter and onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread on small French bread or rye bread rounds.
Place on cookie baking sheet.
Broil until bubbly.
Watch closely.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Turn oven to 425°.
On chicken put salt, pepper, garlic powder and poultry seasoning to taste.
Place margarine in pan and melt in oven.
When margarine is melted, flour chicken and place in pan with margarine.
Bake in oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over and bake another 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add pineapple.
Chill until syrupy.
Add cherry pie filling.

title: shrimp with feta cheese and ouso
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Chop parsley, onion and garlic.
Saute garlic and onion in 1 tablespoon olive oil until soft.
Chop tomatoes; add to mixture with wine and bay leaf.
Crumble Feta cheese and reserve aside.
Cook onion mixture over medium heat until thickened, stirring occasionally (about 20 minutes).
Stir in cream and pepper.
Saute shrimp in 2 tablespoons olive oil separately.
In a small pan, heat ouso carefully until it ignites; shake flames out.
Place shrimp in a shallow baking dish.
