Cover with sauce and ouso.
Sprinkle crumbled Feta cheese over top and bake 10 minutes, until cheese melts.
Remove and sprinkle with parsley for a Greek delight!

title: pecan tasties
directions: Form into small balls and pat into mini-muffin pan.
Makes about 24.

title: turkey olive curry
directions: Brown onions and celery in skillet until slightly cooked. (Brown ground turkey along with onions and celery.)
Add diced turkey, flour, salt, curry and bouillon.
Mix well together.
Add milk, olives and olive juice.
Heat until thickened.

title: quick family favorite
directions: Brown meat, onion, green pepper and celery.
Add water as for brown gravy.
Make thickening and thicken.
Simmer until as thick as desired.
Add the other ingredients.
Serve over cooked rice the first day.
If any is leftover, put in casserole and top with cheese or tomato sauce.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add flour and Jell-O to cake mix.
Mix well and make hole in center.
Add water, oil and strawberries.
Mix with beater.
Add eggs, one at a time, until well mixed.
Bake at 350° in 2 layers for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: jiffy hollandaise
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook and stir over low heat until heated through.
Makes 1 cup of sauce.
Very good and easy to make.
Great for Eggs Benedict.

title: medium white sauce
directions: Melt the margarine in a pan.
Stir in the flour; mix until smooth.
Slowly pour in the milk, stirring until sauce is thickened.
Add the salt.
After this has thickened, continue cooking on low to medium heat for approximately 5 minutes.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: Simmer water and sugar for 5 minutes and cool.
Add juices (have juices cold) and pour over ice in punch bowl.
Slowly add 7-Up.
If desired, decorate with fruit slices.
Makes 7 quarts. Serves 50 to 60.

title: cheese and rice
directions: Mix all together.
Add pepper and paprika, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: crispy cheese puffs
directions: Wipe down peppers, do not wash.
Seed them, and cut in strips. Put in jars.
Pack tight.
Cover with vinegar.
With 1 pint, put in 1/2 teaspoon kosher salt.
With 1 quart, put in 1 teaspoon kosher salt.

title: chicken long rice
directions: Cut up chicken (hekka style).
Soak long rice in warm water for 30 minutes.
Chop celery in fine pieces.
Boil water with chicken pieces.
Add Hawaiian salt, garlic, ginger, sugar, shoyu and celery.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Cut long rice into desired length and add to chicken mixture.
Add green onions and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Add onion and green pepper.
Let stand for 1 hour in water to cover to which the salt has been added.
After 1 hour, drain and add the remaining ingredients.

title: dump salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix all ingredients together well and chill.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 eggs and softened margarine.
Do not beat.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked beans to can
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Next morning, cook until soft.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cold pack 1 1/2 to 2 hours or 95 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: chili casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Mix well.
Then add chili.
Cook until mixture begins to simmer.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand; fold in large tub of Cool Whip. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Add miniature marshmallows if you like. Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil and pour over the remaining ingredients.
Bake in long, greased and floured pan 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mice
directions: Unwrap kiss.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate chips according to directions on bag.
Dip a cherry in chocolate and press against the big flat bottom of kiss as it is turned on its side.
The pointed end of the kiss is the face.
The stem is the tail. Insert two almond slices for ears just between the kiss and cherry.
Makes eyes with very small dots of icing.

title: green salad
directions: Prepare salad greens.
Wash lettuce, romaine and endive. Separate into leaves, discarding discolored or bruised leaves. Drain well, shaking in salad basket or placing on paper towels, to remove excess moisture.
Place cleaned greens in plastic bag or wrap in plastic film.
Refrigerate until crisp and cold, several hours.
Also refrigerate salad bowl.

title: vegetable delicious
directions: Place into baking dish baby lima beans, green beans, peas and bell pepper, cut into strips.
Cover with mayonnaise and sour cream.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas pecan pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat egg yolks until
thick
and
lemon colored.
Add to creamed mixture and blend thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Alternately add egg whites and sifted cake flour.
Beat well after each addition. Fold
in
pecans.
Bake
at
for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Break graham crackers into pieces and line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 sealable container.
Mix pudding according to box directions.
When thickened, blend in Cool Whip with an electric mixer.
Pour half of pudding mixture over graham crackers.
Top with remaining graham crackers and remaining pudding mixture.
Spoon cherry pie filling on top.
Chill.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown meat and add celery; brown a few minutes.
Put in bowl with bread, parsley and beaten egg.
Fill mushrooms and bake in a well buttered pan 1/2 hour or until desired doneness.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut 2 racks of ribs into serving size pieces.
Brown in frypan and put into roaster pan.
Put sauce ingredients in frypan and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour over ribs and bake until done.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed on package. Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute cabbage and green pepper in water until tender.
Melt margarine; combine with stuffing mix.
Place half of the stuffing mix in baking dish.
Layer half of the cabbage, half of the soup and half of the cheese.
Repeat layers of cabbage, soup and cheese.
Add remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Mix noodles together and cook as directed on packages.
Serve with sauce on top of noodles and sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese.

title: cream pie filling
directions: Good for chocolate or coconut.
If chocolate, use 1/3 cup of coca.

title: scalloped potatoes and spinach
directions: In a 2-quart, microwave-safe casserole, micro-cook the sliced potatoes, water and salt, covered, on 100% power for 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are just tender, stirring twice.
Drain. Remove from casserole and set aside.

title: bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water, then scald milk.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and water.
Allow to cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and mix.
Add flour gradually and mix.
Knead dough until spongy, then put in bowl and let rise to double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
Divide in two equal portions.
Form into loaves. Place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: snowball salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Fill container one-inch full and let set. Keep the remainder at room temperature.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Meat sauce:
In a large skillet, brown ground beef in oil. Add garlic, onion, sweet basil, tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 hour; stir occasionally.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with 2 knives.
Mix vinegar, egg and water together.
Add flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Roll into shape and line 9-inch aluminum pans; freeze until needed. Makes 4 crusts.

title: pretzel salad
directions: In a medium bowl, cream together the butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Add pretzels. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sour cream drop cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Combine flour with nutmeg, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add nuts and mix well.
Drop with teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: french onion beef au jus(good, delicious, worth the time)
directions: Lightly brown onion in butter.
Combine soy sauce, garlic, browning sauce, onion soup mix and 5 cups water.
Place roast in 4-quart casserole or Dutch oven.
Add soy sauce mixture and onions.
Cover tightly.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: eggs al agua(boiled eggs)
directions: Pour water into medium size pot.
Heat to boiling.
Place eggs in water, being careful not to burn hands.
Look at clock.
Five to 7 minutes later (that's why you looked at the clock), vary time according to desired doneness, remove eggs from the water, once again being careful not to burn hands.
Place eggs somewhere they will not roll away.
Caution:
Eggs should not be eaten in this state.
If needed, ask for assistance in peeling them first.

title: apricot cheese delight salad
directions: Keep apricot and pineapple juice separated.
Chill fruit. Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add apricot juice and cool.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Chill until firm.
Add topping.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except 7-Up. Add soda just before serving.
Pour over crushed ice.

title: oriental seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet until hot.
Add crab delights and vegetables; cook and stir over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add the garlic powder, ground ginger and seasoning packet.
Stir well. Cook 1 minute longer.
Serve immediately over cooked rice.
Serves 3. Easy to make and delicious!

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Reserve liquid.
Mix juices to make 1 cup.
Add water if needed.
Put 1 cup of juice and 1 cup of water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Dissolve jello in this and add 1 3/4 cup of cold water.
Pour into flat pan.
Add berries and pineapple.
Stir.
Place in refrigerator to gel.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, beat egg slightly.
Add sugar, sour cream, flour, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add apples and stir until well blended.
Turn into unbaked shell.
Bake for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Cover cabbage, onion, and pepper with ice and let stand 30 minutes to 1 hour, then drain cabbage very well and mix.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt. Pour over cabbage and refrigerate.
May adjust amount of salt and vinegar to your taste. Will keep in refrigerator 1 week.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and water.
Set aside to cool.
Chop oranges, apples and cranberries in a food processor.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Will keep 1 week in refrigerator.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake on a greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Do not overbake. Bake only until lightly brown around edges.

title: pop-up rolls
directions: Put a pat of oleo into each muffin tin and melt.
Drop in mixture.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: tamale pie
directions: Fry meat and onions.
After well browned, add the rest of ingredients.
Pour in casserole and cover with cheese; bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stromboli
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese, and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Use French sweet rolls, cut almost in half.
Spoon meat mixture over rolls and then put Mozzarella cheese on top.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Add noodles, tuna and soup all together.
Add salt and pepper.
Then put little dabs of butter over top.
Then bake in oven until brown.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add peanut butter and cream until smooth.
Add sugar and cream until mixture is light and fluffy. Add well beaten eggs and mix well.
Combine all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased 9-inch layer cake pans and bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool and frost with frosting.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into two pie crusts.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cheese triangles
directions: Remove crust from bread slices and cut bread into triangles. Mix all ingredients and spread on triangles.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 150 triangles.

title: melt in your mouth sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, powdered sugar, oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift soda, salt, cream of tartar and flour together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Chill dough. Roll into small balls; then roll in dry jello.
Press down.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Don't brown.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together in saucepan sugar, flour and cocoa. Gradually blend in milk. Cook over low heat until thick and comes to a boil. Stir continuously. Add 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons margarine. Serve over hot buttered biscuits.

title: lime-cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add softened cream cheese. Beat well with electric mixer until well blended.
Add 1 cup fruit juice drained from fruit cocktail.
Add small amount of lemon juice.
Let partly set, then add fruit cocktail, marshmallows and nuts (if desired).
Let set until nearly solid, then fold in Dream Whip (prepared as directed).
Return to refrigerator until completely set.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all together, Makes one 9 x 13 pan and one small pan. Bake 325° for 25 minutes. When cool frost with:

title: squash jelly
directions: Cook squash without water until transparent, 12 to 15 minutes. Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Bring to a boil and cook 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; add jello.
Stir well until dissolved.
Pour into small jelly jars; seal and store on shelf in a cool place.
Makes 8 to 10 small jars.

title: surprise dessert
directions: Mix everything together, except chocolate chips.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator to harden a little bit. Melt chips, then spread over top.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter, both sugars and egg. Add flour into creamed mixture. Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Press 5 peanut halves on top or crisscross with fork tines. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Crumble sausage and mix with cheese.
Add biscuit mix, 1 cup at a time.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
May be frozen at this time.
Bake in preheated 350° to 375° oven for about 13 to 15 minutes, or until light brown.
If frozen, cooking may take a few extra minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: cheese manicotti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine Ricotta, spinach, Parmesan, egg white, nutmeg, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Fill shells with cheese mixture and put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with spaghetti sauce and remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Bake until the cheese has melted and is beginning to brown, about 35 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes; remove from heat.
Quickly stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spoon quickly onto wax paper.

title: rich devils food cake
directions: Combine cocoa, flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon together in a sifter.
Cream sugar, butter and eggs; mix again.
Add vanilla.
Add to mixed dry ingredients and milk until well blended.
Pour into 2 9-inch greased layer cake pans and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with Fluffy Cocoa Frosting.

title: easy cinnamon twists
directions: Roll biscuits into 9-inch long thin roll.
Pinch ends together forming a circle.
Dip in butter, then cinnamon, and sugar.
Form into figure 8's.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese cake cupcakes
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except vanilla wafers.
Line muffin pans with cupcake papers.
Place vanilla wafer in bottom of paper and pour cheese mixture over wafer, approximately 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
When cooled, top with a teaspoon of pie filling (cherry, blueberry, apple, etc.).

title: cheese cracker salad
directions: *I usually make up one package of Dream Whip.
It's more economical.

title: lasagna like
directions: Cook noodles.
Cook meat in a skillet, breaking up lumps.
Add tomato sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat. Combine cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, sour cream, scallions and green pepper.
In casserole, make layers of noodles and the cheese mixture.
Pour the meat sauce over all.
Pour melted butter on top.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and chips.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with mixer until smooth and creamy.
Soften Marshmallow Creme in microwave and add to cream cheese.
Continue blending until mixed.
Stir in food coloring to desired color.
Chill and serve with fresh strawberries or other fresh fruit.

title: toffee bar
directions: In a 2-quart pan, combine butter and sugar.
Stir until it crackles.
Pour into a nongreased cookie sheet.
Lay 4 to 5 Hershey bars on top.
Smooth with a spatula.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Let it cool completely, then break.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Use fresh cucumbers.
Wash and cut in sticks.
Pour boiling water over them and let stand overnight.
Next morning, pack solidly into clean jars.
Make a solution of remaining ingredients.
Boil the solution for 5 minutes.
Pour boiling hot over the cucumbers in jars.
Put on lids, screwing band tight. Process in boiling water bath.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Yields 6 pint jars.
Add green food coloring, if desired, to solution for more color.

title: puree de papas y tuna(cuban cookery - mashed potatoes and tuna fish)
directions: Cut the boiled eggs into small pieces.
Prepare the mashed potatoes according to instructions on package and while still hot add the cream cheese, mayonnaise, three eggs and tuna fish.
Place lettuce leaves in salad bowl, add salad and decorate with remaining boiled egg.
Press olives on top.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Good for buffets.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: refrigerated mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in boiling salt water until tender. Mash.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy. Cool.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Can be used any time within two weeks.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir in barbecue sauce, pepper and onions. Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Spoon on bottom halves of buns and top with sliced cheese and broil until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine mayonnaise, eggs and onion; blend in broccoli.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, bread, beaten egg and salt.
Brown in skillet; drain off fat.
Add soup and water.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add sour cream.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: cherry cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften; mix together.
Use some of the cherry juice to make mixing easier.
Make 2 balls; roll in chopped nuts. Freezes good.
Serve with cinnamon graham crackers.

title: chicken delight
directions: Brown chicken in margarine.
Remove chicken; add mushroom soup, 1 1/2 cans water, mushrooms and juice and onion mix, then add rice.
Pour in casserole.
Place chicken on top and cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: farm rich no cholesterol pumpkin pie
directions: Pour pumpkin, Farm Rich, brown sugar, egg substitute and spices into a blender.
Process at medium speed for 2 minutes.

title: sour cream swiss steak
directions: Roll steak in flour mix.
Brown in Crisco.
Add chopped onions.
Add water and
mix
well.
Gradually
add sour cream. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: heavenly pineapple pie
directions: Whip the cream until stiff.
Refrigerate.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Beat together cream cheese, pudding mix and reserved juice until smooth.
Gently fold
pineapple and whipped cream into pudding.
Spoon filling into pie crust and freeze for 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer to soften 1 hour before serving.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Combine vegetables with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Place remaining ingredients in pan.
Boil for 1 minute.
Cool; drain vegetables.
Add to vinegar mixture.
Stir gently.
Put in containers and freeze.
To use, defrost and serve chilled.

title: zucchini-sausage casserole
directions: Place squash in small amount of water in large saucepan; cover and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Transfer to greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: healthful mustard
directions: Whiz until smooth the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool. Return to blender and add the garlic while whizzing.
Add oil slowly while whizzing.
Chill.

title: mock pierogies
directions: Fry onions in lots of butter.
Have potatoes mashed and on thinner side. Cook macaroni until done.

title: hot shrimp sauce
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine cream cheese and milk.
Add soup and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thoroughly blended and heated.
Add lemon juice and cook 2 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked vegies.
Garnish with chives and slivers of almonds.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart baking dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper. Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until the mixture begins to bubble.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and oleo.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and top with mixture of crackers and oleo. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mrs. stella's chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat and add grated onion.
Add beans and chili.
Then add water (more if desired) and cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Then add tamales and cheese and cook 15 minutes. Serve with pasta or rice.
Fast and easy.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid according to directions on package.
Add strawberries, pineapple and cherries.
Place in freezer until partially frozen.
Pour ginger ale over icy mix before serving.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil all ingredients until chicken is ready to fall apart. Remove all ingredients from broth. Strain broth. Bone chicken and remove cloves.
Return chicken, onion and carrots to broth. Add mixed fresh vegetables. Simmer until vegetables are done.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together. Roll in small balls and freeze. Cook frozen at 325° to 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Add crackers.
Melt margarine in skillet and saute onion and bell pepper.
Add eggs, milk and cheese.
Mix all together and place in greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Brown onion in fat (1 tablespoon).
Mix onion, meats, bread, milk, egg, salt and pepper; mix with hands.
Form into balls. Brown meat balls in same pan to keep balls round.
Remove to hot platter and keep hot.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion in a large frypan until onion is soft. Spoon off fat.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles.
Cover and boil gently for 5 minutes. Break up the thawed spinach into small pieces.
Stir into frypan mixture.
Cover and boil gently 5 minutes.
Stir.
Spoon cottage cheese on top.
Sprinkle with diced cheese.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: quick caramel corn
directions: Boil 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over salted popcorn and stir.

title: alaskan sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (15 x 10-inch) jelly roll pans.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except ice cream at low speed until moistened; beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut each cake into 20 squares. Cut ice cream into 10 slices; cut each slice in half.
Place each ice cream piece between two squares of cake to form sandwich.
Wrap each sandwich tightly with plastic wrap.
Store in freezer.

title: bertha's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except ketchup.
Put in a loaf pan and spread ketchup over the top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar (1/2 cup).
Mix until soft dough forms.
Press into pizza pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Combine cream cheese, juice and 1/2 cup powdered sugar. Cook until thick.
Cool and add 3 cups strawberries.
Spread on crust and serve.

title: peach custard dessert
directions: Grease 9 x
9-inch pan.
Mix baking mix, milk, 3 tablespoons sugar
and	margarine.
Spread in pan.
Arrange peaches on top. Mix
cups
sugar
and	cinnamon.
Sprinkle
over peaches. Mix sour
cream and egg.
Drizzle over top.
Bake at 375° until wooden pick inserted in cake comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Serve
warm and if desired with sweetened whipped cream.

title: confetti slaw
directions: Here's
a
slaw
with a colorful personality, spiced up with a tangy apple taste.
Serves 8.

title: peachy cream salad
directions: Dissolve 1 envelope of D-Zerta in 1 cup of hot water.
Add two-thirds cup cold water and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Chill until thick and place sliced or diced peaches on top.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix well.
Bake on greased
and floured cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, place potatoes.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Spread over potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top of soup/sour cream layer.

title: creamy baked onions
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter; saute onions until lightly brown.
Stir in celery; cook 1 minute longer.
Remove vegetables with a slotted spoon to a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In same skillet, stir in flour; cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat; gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Stir in wine and Tabasco sauce. Return to heat.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir in cheese; then pour sauce over onions.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until onions are tender.
Serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, chocolate, water, milk and eggs.
Mix well; put in vanilla and butter.
Cook until thick.
Put in baked pie crust.
Combine egg whites and beat until foamy, then add about 1/3 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Cook until light brown.

title: deviled crabmeat
directions: Mix half the butter with all the other ingredients except the cheese.
Put in 6 shallow ovenproof ramekins.
Pour remaining butter over them and sprinkle the Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: *french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a small bowl until light and fluffy. Melt chocolate and add it with vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition.
Pour filling into a baked 8-inch pie shell.
Chill until set, about 3 hours.
Spread with whipped cream just before serving.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a two-quart saucepan and simmer 10 minutes.
Make a white sauce of butter, flour and milk and slowly add to tomato mixture, stirring constantly.
Serve at once.

title: strawberry angel torte
directions: Split cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Drain strawberries and combine juice with gelatin.
Let stand 1 minute.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Microcook 2 minutes until sugar and gelatin are dissolved.
Refrigerate for 25 minutes.
Combine gelatin mixture, strawberries and vanilla.
Beat at high speed of electric mixer until light and frothy.
Whip cream and fold into strawberry mixture.
Blend well.

title: lump crab and artichoke casserole
directions: Place all the ingredients into mixing bowl.
Mix.
Place into greased casserole dish, cover the top with seasoned bread crumbs. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then uncover and finish browning, about 15 minutes.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until combined. Beat egg until thick and ivory color.
Beat in milk and vanilla; add to dry ingredients mixture and stir only until smooth. Arrange peaches in a buttered 1 1/2-quart round glass cake dish or similar pan.
Spread batter evenly over peaches.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
(Cake tester should come out clean.)
Serve hot with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, vanilla and confectioners sugar with mixer.
Then by hand mix in Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler.
Dip cooled balls into chocolate mixture with a toothpick. Cool.
Remove toothpick and drizzle top with remaining chocolate.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Dredge pork chops in flour; season with salt and pepper. Brown chops in oil on both sides. Sprinkle with garlic and orange rind. Pour orange juice and gin over chops. Cook, covered, over low heat, turning occasionally until tender. Sauce will thicken.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Gradually add milk and blend well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Blend small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks, then add back into hot mixture in saucepan.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add coconut, butter and vanilla.
Blend well. Cover and cool to lukewarm, stirring occasionally.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Top with meringue or whipped topping.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In a bowl, put the flour, sugar and salt.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the margarine, hot water and Nestle Quik.
Pour over ingredients in bowl and add the eggs, sour cream and baking soda. Mix well.
Pour into large greased cookie sheet with raised edges. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
It usually runs over the pan, so I put some of the batter in a small cake pan to bake.

title: no bake birthday cake
directions: Put saran wrap in inside of bowl so that it will be easy to remove cake after it's frozen.

title: quickie corn pone
directions: Pour chili
into
a large baking dish.	Add drained can of corn.
Mix into
chili.
Mix
cornbread mix per directions. Pour over top of chili.	Bake at
350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cornbread is done.	Sprinkle
shredded cheese and onions on top when serving.
Great with cole slaw and cooked cinnamon apples. Serves 4.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt in top of double boiler.
Add 4 cups oat flakes and toss lightly until thoroughly green.
Then spoon out 1 tablespoon at a time on waxed paper.
Shape into wreaths; add red cinnamon.

title: avocado casserole dip
directions: Layer in 9 x 13 dish in order above.
Chill and serve with chips.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form small balls.
Dip in sugar and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Do not flatten cookies. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients; spread evenly into 10-inch pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce on top.
Place pepperoni on top. Place cheese on.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers or bagel chips.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: venison or beef stew
directions: Cut meat in bite size pieces.
Heat oil.
Add bay leaves; cover.
Let them "crackle," then add meat and brown on all sides. When half done, add onion.
Sprinkle flour over and brown.
Add Guiness and water (add more liquid as needed).
Add parsley and carrots.
Cover and cook in 275° oven about 2 hours.
Stir and add water as needed.
If desired, add prunes last 1/2 hour.
Serves 4.

title: beaumont inn's corn pudding
directions: Stir flour, salt, sugar and butter into corn.
Beat eggs well. Pour into milk, then stir into corn mixture.
Pour into a 2-quart, greased casserole.
Bake in 400°
oven for 40 to 45 minutes, stirring vigorously with a long-tined cooking fork 3 times about 10 minutes apart.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn patties
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper for batter.
Add until you get a good smooth thick batter.
Add corn.
Pour on griddle and fry until golden brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add rest of ingredients. Refrigerate overnight and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash and chop onion; season with salt and margarine. Cook until well done.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased casserole dish.
Save enough cheese and crackers to cover top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
When solid, cover with reserved cheese and crackers and brown slightly.

title: jason's puffed rice bars(child-approved)
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove immediately.
Add peanut butter, water and vanilla.
Stir.
Coat cereal with mixture.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool.
Your treat is here!

title: beef stroganoff
directions: *Two 4 ounce cans may be used.

title: quiche
directions: Bake pie crusts, then baste with yolk of 1 egg and bake 2 more minutes.
Saute bacon and onion.
Beat 4 eggs and add to milk. Add all ingredients together; pour in pie shells and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven when knife comes out clean. Very good.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Heat shortening in hot iron skillet.
Pour mixture in pan.
Place pan in oven on 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until golden.

title: penne ala caprese
directions: Mix together tomato, basil and garlic.
Add olive oil to cover.
Marinate at room temperature or in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, cook penne until al dente. Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Add small amount of olive oil to pasta and stir.
Add pasta to marinated tomato. Bring tomato to room temperature if refrigerated.
Toss with Mozzarella.
Serves 4.

title: scotch scones
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; add shortening and mix very lightly.
Beat eggs until light separately and add to dry ingredients with milk.
Mix slowly to the mixture.
Roll out.
Cut in 2 inch circles.
Brush with milk.
Bake at 425°.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and lemon rind.
Add boiling water. Cook slowly until mixture thickens.
Add egg yolks, lemon juice and butter.
Cook 5 minutes.
Turn into baked pie shells and cover with meringue.
Place into oven to brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry beef; drain off fat.
Add onion, garlic, tomato sauce and olives to beef.
Combine in bowl the sour cream, cottage cheese and green chilies. Crush tortilla chips slightly, reserving a few whole ones for garnish.
Place 1/4 chips in bottom of well buttered or sprayed 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add 1/4 meat mixture; cover with 1/4 sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or cook in microwave for approximately 7 minutes.
Turn and cook 7 minutes more.

title: salmon ala anacortes
directions: You will also need a barbecue, fishing pole, bait (herring is best) and a good fishing spot.

title: fat-free popovers
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Spray a 12 count muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour mixture into muffin tin to 1/2 full.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown. This is a good accompaniment to a soup.
Serves 12.
Calories 53, fat 1 g and cholesterol 41 mg.

title: oven-browned potatoes(microwave)
directions: Heat water, margarine and bouillon together for 1 minute on High.
Stir in potatoes and cook, covered, for 6 minutes on Full Power.
Stir and cook an additional 4 minutes on High.
Stir again.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Quick, easy to make and good.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl; add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into well-greased and lined pans (three 9-inch pans).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Remove from pans immediately and cool completely.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted water until tender.
Put in a casserole dish and add cream of mushroom soup and English peas. Add cheese slices over cauliflower.
Cook in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: fresh peach dumplings
directions: Mix water and sugar in 2 1/2 to 3-quart pan with a tight fitting lid.
Heat to boil.
Add peaches and heat to a boil.
Lay cinnamon rolls, cinnamon side down closely over top of peaches. Cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Spread icing over cinnamon dumplings.
Serve warm with peaches from pan spooned over dumplings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: edible play dough for children
directions: Mix into dough.
Kids will play with it, shape it in many ways, then eat it.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until tender; drain.
Add crumbs, reserving 1 tablespoon for topping.
Add cheese, egg, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining crumbs and dot with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1-quart baking dish.
Combine all ingredients, reserving about 1/2 cup crumbs.
Turn into prepared dish or spoon into baking shells (may be frozen at this point).
Sprinkle 1/2 cup buttered crumbs over top.
Spoon 4 to 5 tablespoons milk over top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: icebox slaw
directions: Set cabbage and onions aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and onions.
Stir well.
Let cool and store in refrigerator in a container with tight fitting lid.
Stores well.

title: pork chops and tomatoes
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Pour rice over pork chops.
Pour tomatoes over rice and one can of water over the tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to slight boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until rice is done (about 20 to 30 minutes).

title: tuna melts
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients.
Fill rolls with 1/3 cup tuna mixture.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: chicken, potatoes and gravy in one
directions: Cut 1 chicken up and place in a long casserole pan.
Peel potatoes and dice over chicken (quarter).
Salt to taste.
Cover with cream of chicken soup.
Cover pan with tinfoil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: calico beans
directions: Use pork and beans as is, juice and beans.
Drain juice from other beans and save.
If mixture is too thick, add later.
Cut bacon in small pieces and brown.
Fry onion until lightly browned and brown hamburger last.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
I prefer to bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Do not overcook!

title: casserole steak
directions: Lay steak on bread board.
Combine flour, salt and pepper. Pound into steak.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Brown in
hot shortening.
Place in a casserole.
Mix catsup and water.
Pour over steak.
Top with onion and green pepper rings.
Put clove in center of each lemon slice.
Arrange across top of casserole. Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Dissolve flour in cold water.
Cook in double boiler.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add egg whites on top.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Simmer onion in butter until soft. Put broccoli in microwave in the box about 1 minute. Remove the box and bend it to break broccoli into pieces. Drain. Mix all ingredients. Lightly oil a 10 x 13 baking pan. Pour in the mixture and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares when cooled.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Add just enough milk to mix by hand.
Form into balls and flatten with fork.

title: lemon jelly pie
directions: Beat
eggs
slightly, enough to blend yolks and whites. Add butter, 1 cup syrup, juice and rind; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake
at
to	325° until filling is set and crust is	brown.	Top
with
whipped
cream
sweetened with 2 tablespoons of syrup.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese lightly.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
(We like it unbaked, also.)

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Combine and cream until smooth sugar, brown sugar, shortening and peanut butter.
Add the egg, vanilla and water.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Stir in the chocolate chips. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° to 375° (bars get golden brown).
Cool well before cutting.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin lemon slices and set aside.
Squeeze juice from the remaining lemon and set aside.
In a skillet, heat the vegetable oil; add chicken and brown.
Remove chicken from pan and set aside.
In skillet, combine soup, milk, lemon juice and pepper.
Add broccoli and heat to boil.
Return chicken to skillet and top with lemon slices.
Cover and cook on low heat for 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve with rice.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Bake in hollowed out French loaf at 325° for about 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Wash cabbage.
Remove bad spots.
Shred with kraut cutter or knife (not too finely).
Layer cabbage in crock.
Sprinkle on salt.
Do in layers until a ratio of 5 pounds of cabbage to 3 1/2 tablespoons salt is used.
Add enough water just to cover cabbage.
Place plain plate or glass pie plate on cabbage.
Place a stone on plate heavy enough to keep cabbage down in liquid. Cover with cheesecloth.

title: lazy day cabbage rolls
directions: Shred cabbage as for coarse slaw.
Put in casserole dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Brown beef and rice.
Drain fat. Stir in onion soup mix.
Pour over cabbage.
Combine tomato soup and water.
Pour over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain off all juice from first 6 ingredients.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour mix over vegetables and beans.
Let set overnight.
Dip salad out of mix.

title: wendy's frosties
directions: Take ice cream from freezer and let stand in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Blend all ingredients and enjoy.

title: lemon glazed wheat germ balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended. Beat in molasses.
Mix together flour, wheat germ, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt.
Stir into first mixture and add raisins and/or walnuts.
Spread in greased 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Put pan on wire rack and spread with following Lemon Glaze while still hot.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Store in an airtight container.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Mix and put rhubarb, sugar, Jell-O and marshmallows in greased large baking pan or 2 smaller ones.
Pour cake batter over rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° until done, a little longer than specified on cake mix.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar, potatoes and shortening together and add milk.
Mix well.
Roll and cut as regular biscuits.
Bake in moderate oven at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Butter while hot and serve at once.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil & oranges together. Grease & flour 2 round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 min. Mix pudding (dry) & cool whip together. Add drained pineapple. Add juice if icing is too dry. Let cake cool spread icing on cake. Keep refrigerated.

title: strawberry fluff salad
directions: Heat pineapple until hot.
Add jello; beat well and mix (do not boil).
Remove from heat; let cool to room temperature.
Add cottage cheese; mix well.
Refrigerate until soft gelled, then fold in Cool Whip so that mixture is slightly thawed when folded in well.
Spoon into clear bowl (should look mounded). Refrigerate.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Whip 3 egg whites with baking powder until almost stiff. Slowly add sugar and beat until peaks.
Fold in pecans and Ritz. Bake in greased pie pan for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
At serving time put on strawberries and Cool Whip.
Serves 6.

title: lemonade salad
directions: Combine pineapple, milk and lemonade. Fold in whipped topping along with marshmallows.
Cover and chill until serving time.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain and mix with all other ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs (Club) or potato chips.

title: finadene sauce
directions: Mash hot peppers to obtain the hot taste.
Depending on "hotness" desired, mash a few or all.
This will keep in the refrigerator.
Some local ladies prefer to add the onions fresh just before serving.
Goes well with most everything.
(I even think it is used on ice cream.) Yields 1 scant cup.

title: butterscotch apple dip
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat combine milk, chips and salt. Cook and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar and cinnamon.
Serve warm with apples.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.
Also good on ice cream.

title: "bilodi" black-eyed pea salad
directions: Soak peas 6 hours, then cook with fresh water 45 minutes. (Optional:
Use 1 pound canned black-eyed peas, drained.) After draining black-eyed peas, add all other ingredients except dressing.
Toss well, then add dressing.
Toss lightly.
Chill. Makes about 7 cups.

title: smoked turkey
directions: Soak hickory chips in water several hours or overnight.
Place charcoal in bottom of smoker.
Start fire and let burn 30 minutes or until briquettes are beginning to gray.
Remove hickory chips; save water.
Place chips directly on hot coals.
Fill water pan with hickory water plus enough to make 6 quarts.
Season turkey, inside and out, and place on rack.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 hours. Weather conditions will affect your results.
This recipe is based on a 50° temperature or higher.
Very cold weather will require a longer cooking time.

title: fresh peach pie or strawberry
directions: Blend and cook until thick.
Stir constantly.
In baked pie shell, sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar and add 1 quart of fresh fruit. Pour glaze over fruit and refrigerate.
I like whipped topping on mine.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with oleo; cook zucchini slightly and drain well. Combine zucchini, half the stuffing mixture, carrots, onion, soup and sour cream.
Place in lightly greased baking dish. Sprinkle other half of stuffing mixture over top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and add 1 1/2 pounds of oleo.
Enough for 12 chickens.

title: alice morgan's savory oven pot roast
directions: Chop or grind lamb coarsely, using lean and fat meat in equal portions.
Salt accordingly.
Cook over medium heat until done. Stir occasionally.
May be stored in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and eggs.
Add brown sugar and white sugar, then stir in flour.
Mix in M&M's and dip out by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain well.
Add sugar, raisins, nuts, salt and eggs.
Melt butter in baking pan (about 8 x 12-inch).
Grease pan; pour rest in noodle mixture.
Blend well and spread mixture in baking pan.
Sprinkle evenly with cinnamon. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 55 minutes or until browned. Very good warm or cold.
Try with diced apples.

title: clam chowder
directions: Dice potatoes.
Brown salt pork in a 2-quart pot.
Add onions, potatoes and chopped clams.
Cover with clam juice and water. Bring to a boil and then simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: "chicken breast italiano"
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Place in shallow bowl.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Coat well, cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Combine remaining ingredients except oil. Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Fry chicken, turning once about 30 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel and enjoy.
Can be doubled for large group.

title: fruit compote
directions: Mix all fruits together; then stir in pudding mix.

title: diet spice tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in jar with tight fitting lid until needed. Use 1 teaspoon in a cup of hot water.
One teaspoon of mix equals 1 calorie.

title: never fail noodles
directions: Measure flour, add baking powder and salt; then add cream, lard and eggs.
Make into dough and roll out thin.
Cut and let lay on board for 2 hours.
Cook in ham broth for 30 minutes.

title: crab souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain. Cut up in slices: green pepper, red onion (little onions) and tomatoes.
Add to pasta.
Sprinkle Salad Supreme, garlic powder and dash of vinegar.
Toss.
Pour Seven Seas dressing over and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: foolproof popovers
directions: Beat eggs and milk lightly with wire whisk or fork.
Stir in flour and beat only enough to mix in salt and flour.
(Don't worry about lumps.)

title: extra easy lasagna
directions: Puree tomatoes with tomato paste in blender until smooth. Stir in parsley, oregano and basil; set aside.
Break up sausage. Add onion and garlic in skillet.
Cook well browned.
Pour off fat.
Stir 1/2 spaghetti sauce mix into sausage mixture.
Spoon sausage mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Spoon cottage cheese evenly over sausage.
Arrange noodles on top. Sprinkle noodles with remaining spaghetti mix.
Pour tomato mixture over noodles.
Press down until moistened.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until noodles are tender. Remove foil.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: cauliflower mountain
directions: Place whole head of cauliflower, stem end down, in an 8-inch glass pie plate.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 7 to 8 minutes, or until tender.
Mix mayonnaise and prepared and dry mustards in a bowl.
Pour mixture over top of cooked cauliflower. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Microwave at High for 1 minute to melt cheese.
Serves 4.

title: unusual cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Add salt.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Add Raisin Bran, nuts, dates and oatmeal (dough will be crumbly). Shape into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with floured fingers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and remove from sheet.
Makes about 2 1/2 or 3 dozen.

title: raspberry-topped lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch; cook and stir until thickened and clear.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened milk and food coloring. Pour into crust.
Bake for 30 minutes, then spoon raspberry mixture over top.
Chill 4 hours, or until set.
Spread whipped cream over top and serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 pie.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Saute onion, melt cheese, add soup, add cabbage and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Cover and chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls, roll in sugar and place about 3-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until set but not hard.
Place an unwrapped Hershey's Kiss in center of each cookie.
Cool on rack.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Grease the bottom only of a 9 1/4 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan; set aside.
Combine all ingredients, except chips and walnuts, in a large mixer bowl.
Blend well on medium speed.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs, then hot water.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add oatmeal, nuts, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet corned beef and cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and corned beef together, breaking up meat as it cooks.
Add cabbage and cover.
Steam for a few minutes.
(Cabbage will have retained some water from having been washed.)
Stir occasionally, adding water to prevent sticking, until cabbage is done to your liking.
Add margarine, salt and pepper.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Combine in glass bowl for microwave or crock-pot or pan on top of stove.
Heat until cream cheese is melted, stirring until blended.
Serve with corn chips.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressings and cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill.

title: chocolate raspberry torte
directions: Bake in 8-inch pans either round or square.
Prepare cake according to package directions.
After cake is completely cooled, slice both cakes horizontally.
You should have 4 thin cakes.
Ice bottom layer.
Spread 1/3 of raspberry preserves over top of icing; leave 1/2-inch of edge.
Repeat procedure with 2nd and 3rd. Ice with remaining icing.

title: louisiana  special pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and two eggs.	Blend well.
Spread in a well greased 13x9 aluminum pan.
Then beat cream cheese (room temperature) until fluffy.	Add 2 eggs, vanilla and confectioners' sugar.
Blend well.
Pour over cake and sprinkle nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle reserve, 1/2 c. confectioners' sugar while the cake is still hot.
Cool before cutting or cake will crumble.
Overnight is best before cutting.

title: squash pickles
directions: Prepare squash, onions and salt and cover with ice for 3 hours.
Heat the sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, turmeric and celery seed, then add squash and onions.
Bring to a boil, put in jars and seal.

title: baked pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread, cubed.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Terrific with ham!

title: eclair pie
directions: Bring to a boil the water, margarine and salt.
Remove from heat.
Add the flour; mix well.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time.
Mix well each time.
Spread onto round cookie sheet.
Make sides higher than middle.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven; let set in oven with door open for 15 minutes.
Mix the instant pudding, 1 cup milk and the heavy cream.
Beat for 3 minutes. Pour onto crust.
Microwave the chocolate frosting for 45 seconds; stir, then pour over top.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: seafood salad mold
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in mold (or bowl). Refrigerate overnight.

title: best ever rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add flour and cake mix.
Mix all together with your hands.
Leave in container and cover.
Let rise until double in size.
Flour surface and pour dough onto it. Knead only enough to make into biscuits.
Don't work extra flour into it.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mystery pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, nuts, pineapple and fruit salad.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread in pie shells.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: * Frozen, unsugared blueberries or unsugared canned, drained blueberries work nicely too.

title: kirt's casserole
directions: Cook and drain the noodles.
Add browned hamburger and onion to the remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, or microwave for 10 minutes.

title: have it your way brisket
directions: In the oven:
Sprinkle a bit of the onion soup mix in the bottom of a baking dish; rub Kitchen Bouquet and dry spices into brisket.
Place brisket in dish and cover with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator overnight. Next day, preheat oven to 350°.
Remove plastic wrap and cover brisket with foil.
Cook brisket 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Let stand for 20 minutes or so; slice and watch it disappear.

title: lite chicken enchiladas
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with cooking spray. In medium bowl, combine sour cream, yogurt, soup and chilies and mix well. Spoon 3 tablespoons sour cream mixture down center of each tortilla. Reserve 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese. Add cheese over mixture in each tortilla. Roll and place in baking dish, seam down. Spread remaining sour cream mixture over tortillas. Cover and bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Remove foil and sprinkle with reserved cheese. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes. Serve on top of shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes with 1/2 cup salsa per person. Serves 6.
tags: Healthy Choice cream of mushroom soup

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In a large bowl or plastic bag, coat beef cubes with 1/4 cup flour.
In a large skillet or Dutch oven, brown meat and onions in hot oil. Stir in paprika, salt, marjoram, pepper, green pepper, garlic, 1/2 cup water and tomatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 2 hours or until meat is tender. Combine 3 tablespoons flour with 1/2 cup water. Stir into hot liquid.
Heat mixture until it boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Serve over noodles.

title: sweet chocolate smiles
directions: In mixer bowl, cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
In food processor or electric blender, combine flour and 2/3 cup of the walnuts.
Process to grind walnuts.
Stir into creamed mixture with chocolate chips and remaining walnuts.
Shape dough into crescents (smiles).
Place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes or until edges are golden.
Cool on racks.
Dust cookies with powdered sugar to coat.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Place 6 slices of bread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch ungreased dish.
Cook the sausage.
Drain.
Place sausage on top of the bread.
Mix together the eggs, milk, salt and cheese.
Pour over the sausage.
Let set overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn and beaten eggs; salt and pepper. Add all other ingredients as listed. Bake in greased casserole at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk and egg yolks; heat until hot.
In bowl, mix sugar, flour and chocolate.
Add to hot mixture.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well with a fork (do not beat).
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 1/4 hours in a greased tube pan.

title: fruit 'n cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fruits, in blender until smooth, about 1 minute.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours.
To serve, mound cheese dip in small bowl and place on tray with fruits for dipping.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Batter beef tips in flour.
Brown in grease in large skillet. Drain.
Place meat in crock-pot.
Mix soup together.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low all day until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in floured pan (cookie sheet).

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix cornbread according to directions.

title: summer cool salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
In another bowl, combine jello and cottage cheese, then add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Chill.
Great for dessert or as a cool salad with a sandwich.
(Do not dissolve jello in water.
Add dry jello mix to cottage cheese.)

title: baked chicken
directions: Place drained broccoli in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add undiluted soups over broccoli.
Place chicken over soup.
Add Mozzarella cheese over chicken.
Sprinkle onions on top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups of boiling water.
Add the crushed pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Mix well.
Pour into a square dish or pretty mold.
Chill until firm.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Stir in milk only until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto chicken or meat in boiling meat stock.
Cook 10 minutes with kettle uncovered and 10 minutes tightly covered.
Remove dumplings and meat to hot platter.
Keep hot while making gravy.
Pour part of gravy around them.
Serve the remainder separately.
My family's favorite.

title: catfish provencale
directions: Slice the onion and cut the tomatoes into narrow wedges. Saute lightly in one tablespoon of butter.
Place fillets in a baking dish so they do not overlap.
Sprinkle fish with oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Dot fish with butter.
Spoon onions and tomatoes over fish.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Season the tomato juice with salt and pepper.
Heat the juice and add jello.
Dissolve and stir.	Add vegetables to jello and pour into mold when nearly set.

title: peppered rib-eye steaks
directions: Brush steaks lightly with olive oil.
In small bowl, combine all seasonings.
Sprinkle seasonings over steaks and press into both sides.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Grill steaks to desired doneness.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine and put in pie dish.
Top with slivered almonds and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: slush
directions: Mix and blend first 6 ingredients.
Add 7-Up.
Freeze in serving cups.
Thaw 30 to 45 minutes before serving.
Good served with cookies.
Keeps 2 or 3 weeks frozen.

title: turnip pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover and cook over medium heat 40 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.

title: easy rolls
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Heat water, milk and cooking oil in saucepan over low heat until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add egg to warm liquid and flour mixture.
Blend at low speed with mixer 3 minutes, then 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in another 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour by hand to form a stiff batter (batter will follow spoon).
Cover batter and let rise in a warm place (80° to 85°) until light and doubled, about 50 minutes.
Stir down batter, then spoon into greased muffin cups or muffin pan. This dough should rise about 20 minutes, then bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately after baking.

title: old world raspberry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients, except raspberry preserves.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes).
Reserve 1 1/2 cups mixture and set aside.
Press remaining mixture into greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Spread preserves to within 1/2-inch from edge.
Crumble reserved 1 1/2 cups mixture over preserves.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: pineapple surprise cake
directions: Put crushed pineapple, 1 1/4 cups sugar, flour, egg, soda and salt in a bowl; mix with a fork.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan (batter will be thin) . Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven.
While still hot, sprinkle with coconut and chopped nuts.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In glass mixing bowl, combine peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt. Cook on High (100% power) 7 to 9 minutes until mixture is bubbling and peanuts are brown. Quickly stir in butter and vanilla. Cook on High 2 to 3 minutes longer. Add baking soda. Stir quickly just until mixture is foamy. Pour immediately onto greased baking sheet. Let cool about 15 minutes until firm. Break peanut brittle into pieces. Store in an airtight container.

title: leon's vegetable casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Put in bottom of large casserole dish.
Saute vegetables in butter to coat.
Add wine, soy sauce and water; cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Use slotted spoon to transfer vegetables to casserole dish over top of rice.
I add a small amount of the liquid.
Spread sour cream on top of vegetables.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of sour cream. Then top with cashews.
Place under broiler until cheese melts. Serves 5 to 6 as a main dish or 8 to 10 as a side dish.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Put these ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan in the order listed.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add milk and butter.
Sprinkle nutmeg. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake in 350° oven.
Remove from oven when center is slightly soft.

title: mom's one egg cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream Crisco, sugar, egg and lemon extract together.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: overnite caramel french toast
directions: Combine sugar, butter and corn syrup in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour syrup in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place 6 slices of bread on top of syrup mixture.
Top with remaining 6 slices of bread.
Combine eggs, milk, vanilla and salt, stirring until blended.
Pour egg mixture evenly over bread slices.
Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix syrup, vinegar, salad oil, sugar and mustard; stir until well mixed.
Add to cool carrots, onion and green pepper.
Pour the soup mix over carrot mixture.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: cream cake
directions: Beat 1 egg and 1 1/2 cups sugar together, then add 1/2 cup sifted flour; wet with a little milk to make perfectly smooth. Stir all of this into 1 pint boiling milk.
It is best to put the milk into a double boiler to prevent it from burning.
Flavor with vanilla and lemon flavorings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Lightly butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover bottom with bread cubes.
Brown sausage in a skillet, breaking up meat with a fork while browning.
Drain and spread over bread cubes.
Put milk, salt, mustard and eggs in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over sausage and top with grated cheese.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.
This is also good for supper served with green beans and sliced tomatoes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine ground chuck, onion, celery, green pepper, egg, and 1/2 cup ketchup.
Mix thoroughly.
Add bread, crumbled.
Place in microwavesafe loaf pan.
Mix 1/2 cup ketchup and brown sugar. Place on top of meat loaf.
Microwave meat loaf 20 to 25 minutes on Medium-high powder.
Drain grease.
Microwave 10 minutes on High powder.
Rotate meat loaf occasionally throughout cooking.

title: blueberry salad
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan mix gelatin and boiling water until dissolved.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Stir and let set. Separately mix sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Spread on top of gelatin mixture when set and sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, sour cream, butter, milk and eggs together.
Add muffin mix.
Then pour in baking dish: sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican skillet dinner
directions: Use a large skillet.
Cook ground beef and onion until almost done.
Add rice.
Continue cooking until ground beef is done and rice is browning.
Add envelope of taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Add tomato paste along with 3/4 cup water.
Allow this to cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender.
Add kidney beans and corn.
Mix.
Allow to simmer 15 minutes more over low heat.
Serves 6 to 8 easily.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Grind peppers and onions.
Add to first mixture.
Bring to a boil and cook until thick.
Salt to taste.
Remove from heat and stir in oleo.
Mix well. Seal in hot pint jars.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix ingredients in gallon glass jar.
Slit vanilla beans French-style.
Scrape out seeds.
Add to mixture.
Stir every other day for 4 weeks.
Strain and bottle.

title: cantaloupe-orange frost
directions: Advance preparation:
Combine milk, dairy sour cream and sugar in blender container.
Add cantaloupe pieces.
Cover and blend on high speed for 10 seconds.
Chill well.

title: german pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Butter well two 9-inch pie pans. Put eggs into blender; cover and process at stir until light yellow in color. Push mix button; remove cover and add remaining ingredients. Process until smooth. Pour into prepared pans and bake for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes. Slide onto hot plates. Serve with lemon slices, powdered sugar and butter.
Syrup, jelly, honey or flavored butter may also be used. Yield: Two 9-inch pancakes.

title: macaroni and ham casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice potatoes; add onion (chopped) and parsley to taste. Blend together oil and flour in saucepan.
Stir in sugar, water, vinegar and salt and pepper (to taste).
Cook (low heat) until boils, stirring constantly.
Pour hot over cold potatoes, onion and parsley.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Add milk, melted shortening and yeast to sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well, form into soft ball.
Put in refrigerator for 12 hours, punching down if it rises.
Roll out on floured board and use as desired.
Keep unused dough in refrigeration.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions.
Bring crushed pineapple to a boil.
When cake is done, poke holes in top of cake; pour pineapple over cake while still warm.
When cool, slice bananas over top of cake.
Make vanilla pudding according to package directions; spread over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with coconut and crushed nuts.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion and oleo. Mash cooked squash. Crumble cornbread all over other ingredients. Beat eggs and add to mixture. Add soup, salt and pepper to taste. Cook for 30 minutes or until golden brown with firm texture at 375°.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and egg.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Cool.
Cook macaroni product as directed on package. Rinse, drain and cool.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until just tender.
Drain and mix with all other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9 inch pan. Add layer of crumbs, layer of chocolate chips, layer of coconut, layer of pecans. Pour Eagle Brand milk over top. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dilute Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water; let chill until partially firm.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions; add Jell-O.
Whip until blended.
Add sliced bananas; stir.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and oleo.
Add beaten yolks.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla and buttermilk with dry ingredients. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add coconut and pecans.
Use 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a double boiler.
Heat until all ingredients are blended.
Dip apple slices into hot caramel mixture.
Very delicious.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Peel one orange.
Grate oranges, apples and cranberries. Prepare jello to package directions.
Mix all and let set overnight.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix all ingredients together.

title: london broil
directions: Marinate for 3 hours.
Cook 15 minutes per side for medium rare.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water; add hot water.
Add pineapple and juice, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Let stand overnight. Whip 2 packages Dream Whip and mix with gelatin mixture.
Using a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass salad dish, layer angel food pieces and gelatin mixture.
Continue layers, finishing with cake.
Ice with 1 package of Dream Whip.
Decorate with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut (optional).

title: celery sizzle
directions: Simmer celery in water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup, water chestnuts with juice and celery.
Put in a casserole and top with buttered crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6; 125 calories per serving.

title: sweet and spicy ribs
directions: Combine short ribs with all ingredients except onions, in a large saucepan; cover.
Simmer 2 hours or until tender.
Cool; then chill until 1 1/4 hours before serving time.
Skim off fat; remove bay leaf.
Place meat in a baking dish.
Pour sauce over. Top with onion slices.
Cover.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Baste onions with sauce.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: hot chocolate dry mix
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Store for daily use.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.
Makes 1 large Tupperware bowl of mix.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water, then add rest of water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Beat in flour, one cup at a time, until smooth,
Knead the remaining flour in on a hard, flour-covered board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, not sticky. Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down and let rest 10 minutes.
Divide into 2 loaves and place in greased bread pans.
Let rise to double size again.
Bake at 425° until light brown, approximately 30 minutes, until bread sounds hollow when tapped on.

title: sticky buns
directions: (Prepare late in the evening for baking in the morning.) Partially thaw bread dough.
Slice in half lengthwise; cut each half into 6 pieces.
Spray or grease bottom of tube pan.
Place in bottom of pan the chopped nuts and raisins.
Place bread dough pieces on top.
Blend pudding mix and cinnamon and sprinkle over bread pieces.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar; add molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Roll in small balls; dip in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Dough works better if refrigerated for an hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cooked mashed pumpkin with milk and sugar.
Add oil and molasses.
Mix the cornstarch with the spices and stir in.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a hot oven (425°) for ten minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 to 50 minutes until filling is set in the middle.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix together and let stand until firm.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in small bowl and set aside.
In larger bowl, combine Crisco and sugars and mix until smooth.
Add vanilla and water and mix well.
In small cup beat eggs and then add to mix.
Slowly add flour mixture and when well combined, add chocolate chips.
Place large spoonful on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place cookies on racks to cool.

title: twinkie pudding
directions: Split Twinkies longways to line the size baking dish you want to use.
Mix instant pudding according to package directions and pour over split Twinkies.
Cut bananas into slices and spread on top of pudding.
Then crumble crushed drained pineapple over top of bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts (if desired). Refrigerate.

title: meat casserole
directions: Place bread, buttered side down, in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Layer meat.
Add soup and mayonnaise.
Spread over meat.
Add layer of bread, buttered side up.
Spread beaten eggs and milk over top. Add grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hominy pie
directions: Brown meat in hot fat.
Add flour, tomatoes and seasonings. Brown hominy and onion, then put together and cook in casserole dish after sprinkling with cheese.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters and roll in mixture of 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Put in greased Bundt pan. Melt margarine; add 3/4 cup of sugar and 3/4 teaspoon of cinnamon. Heat until sugar melts and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool, then put on plate.

title: spiced baked ham slice
directions: Slash outside fat about 1-inch apart to prevent curling. Stick whole cloves around edge of ham.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over ham slice in shallow pan or baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Serve with green peas and broiled grapefruit slices, bananas or peach halves sprinkled with cinnamon or nutmeg. Serves 4 to 5.

title: angel biscuits
directions: In a small bowl, soften the yeast with the warm water and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
With a pastry cutter, cut in the shortening until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Add the yeast mixture and the buttermilk and stir well until combined.
On a floured board, knead about 2 minutes or until smooth, adding more flour as needed.
Roll out the dough to 1/2 inch thickness.
Using a 2-1/2 inch biscuit cutter, cut out 24 biscuits.
At this point either bake the biscuits or, for a roll-like texture, let them rise 45 minutes and then bake at 450° for about 8 minutes.

title: tenderloin deluxe
directions: Remove surface fat and connective tissue from meat; spread with 2 tablespoons butter.
Place on rack in shallow roasting pan. Cook 15 minutes, then baste in sauce.
Insert meat thermometer. Roast at 425° until 140° (rare).
For 2 to 3 pounds about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: baked meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk; crumble.
Add meat, baking powder, onion and poultry seasoning.
Mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. Cut garlic in half and cook in margarine a few minutes.
Remove garlic; add meatballs and brown.
Pour off excess fat.
Add soup and water; bring to boil.
Put into casserole dish and bake in moderate oven at 350° about 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: new york egg cream
directions: All ingredients must be cold.
