Measure syrup into tall glass; stir in cream to blend.
Slowly pour club soda down side of glass, stirring constantly.
Serve immediately.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix well the vinegar, oil and mustard; add onion.
Grind pepper over top and stir.
Marinate steak in mixture for 2 to 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Charcoal as steak!

title: tuna bunwiches
directions: Melt margarine; add tuna and lightly brown.
Add onion, mushroom soup and milk.
Chop hard-boiled egg fine and stir into mixture.
Serve on toasted bun or English muffin.

title: quiche lorraine appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry as directed on package. Roll 1/16-inch thick on lightly floured board. Cut into 1 1/2 to 2-inch rounds. Fit rounds into tiny muffin tins. (May need to adjust size to fit tin used.)
Combine bacon, cheese and onion. Fill each cup with approximately 1 tablespoon of mixture. Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in remaining ingredients. Pour 1 tablespoon of cream mixture into each cup over bacon mixture. Bake at

375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown. Let cool in pans for 5 minutes before removing. Can also make 1 or 2 days ahead. Wrap in foil and reheat at 350° for 10 minutes before serving. Makes 36 pieces.

title: fanned-roasted potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice 1/4-inch without cutting through the other side. Place in bowl of cold water. Spray an 11 x 7-inch baking pan with Pam.
Place potatoes in pan, cut side up.
Brush with margarine.

Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Italian seasoning. One hour before serving, bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Baste with margarine. Increase temperature to 450° and bake 20 minutes more, testing for doneness.
Garnish with parsley (optional).

title: apple pound cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture, beating well.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Let cake cool in pan 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, milk and oleo.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick like custard.
Remove.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.

title: broccoli-green bean casserole
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise, onion, eggs and cheese.
In greased casserole, place half of the broccoli.
Put all of the beans on top.
Pour half of the sauce on top of the beans and then add remaining broccoli, then remaining sauce. Cover with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pilaf
directions: Heat the oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add onion, garlic, and celery and saut for 2-3 minutes. Add rice and saut until brown.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine boiling water and oats; let stand for 10 minutes.
Add sugar and margarine until margarine melts.
Add all other ingredients and 1/2 package chocolate chips. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 25 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle other 1/2 package of chips on top and smooth to make frosting.

title: moca froth
directions: Heat coffee and cocoa together.
Do not boil!
Pour into cups; top with whipped cream and grate chocolate over the top.
Serves 2.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well. Chill. Serve with your favorite fresh vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Crush Butterfingers and set aside. Tear angel food cake into small pieces. Beat egg yolks until well mixed. Melt margarine and add to egg yolks, then add powdered sugar and Cool Whip. In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer the cake, then egg mixture, then top with crushed Butterfingers.

title: brandied candied cranberries
directions: Place cranberries in large, flat baking pan.
Berries should be in a single layer.
Sprinkle with the sugar.
Cover tightly with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool; sprinkle with the brandy or cognac.
Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator, or may be frozen.
Reheat, covered, in oven or microwave.
Delicious with poultry.

title: turtle candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and oleo.
Cook 7 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Time carefully.
Pour mixture over pecans, chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir until chips melt, about 1 minute.
Spoon on waxed paper.
Makes 5 1/2 pounds.

title: jack's favorite chocolate chip cookie
directions: Blend flours, soda, baking powder and oats in medium bowl. Soften margarine or butter in large bowl, blend in sugars, eggs, vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.
Gradually blend dry ingredients into butter mixture.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 400° for approximately 8 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: won tons and sauce
directions: Chop onion and water chestnuts; mix all ingredients together and place 1 teaspoon in the center of a Won Ton skin. Moisten edges with water and seal to form a triangle. Deep fry in 4 cups oil until golden brown. Serve with Won Ton Sauce.

title: sunshine salad
directions: First, put first 5 ingredients in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Let set to consistency of egg white.
Add the carrots, pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate until firm.

title: special popcorn
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and corn syrup together for 5 minutes. Add baking soda.
Pour mixture over 2 bags of hulless popcorn in a large aluminum roaster.
Mix well.
(I divide this into 2 roasters.)
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Add one cup of peanuts, if desired.
This recipe makes a lot, but it disappears really fast!
Great to bag for holiday gift giving.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the cake mix, pudding, oil and milk.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each one.
Fold in chocolate chips, German chocolate and nuts.
Pour into Bundt or tube pan and bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool cake in pan ten minutes before turning out.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg yolks. Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg white with 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla until stiff. Pour on top of pie and put into oven until browned.

title: beaumont inn corn pudding
directions: Stir into the corn the flour, salt, sugar and butter.
Add well-beaten eggs to milk and stir into the corn.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart shallow pan and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Stir from bottom 3 times while cooking.

title: swiss potatoes
directions: Butter a casserole and rub it with the garlic.
Peel and thinly slice the potatoes. Arrange in layers in casserole, sprinkling each layer with salt, pepper, nutmeg, sliced green onions and shredded Swiss cheese.
Scald the milk and slowly add the egg yolk.
Pour over the potatoes and dot with butter. Bake 1 hour or more at 350°.

title: crock-pot wieners
directions: Cut hot dogs in two and wrap with bacon. Secure with toothpicks. Put hot dogs in crock-pot and cover with brown sugar. Cook on low for 4 hours or until bacon is done.

title: fast pepper steak
directions: Brown and drain meat. Add onion and pepper. Cook 15 minutes. Add soy sauce and gravy. Simmer on low heat about 20 minutes. Serve on seasoned rice.

title: lo-cal coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, celery, carrot, green onion and parsley.
Pour on salad oil and toss until slaw is evenly coated.
Sprinkle on and toss in the seasonings:
salt, pepper, celery salt and monosodium glutamate which will now stick to the oil coated slaw.
Finally add wine vinegar and toss.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat; combine spaghetti, meat, tomatoes, celery, carrots and onions in 11 x 15 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients except cheese in saucepan.
Heat, pour over spaghetti mixture and mix well.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour or until carrots are done.
Top with cheese during last 2 or 3 minutes of baking.

title: southern cotton cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges with juice, 4 eggs, oil and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use 2 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: quickie butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sugar. Cool slightly.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to sugar mixture with other ingredients.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into a greased and floured 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cook rice and drain.
Add soup mix, mushroom soup, bell pepper, rice, salt and pepper together.
Pour into loaf pan and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1/2 cup.
Combine gelatin and boiling water in blender.
Cover and blend at low speed 1 minute, then add reserved liquid, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Blend with electric mixer, at high speed 1 minute.
Fold in fruit; garnish with nuts, if desired.
Pour in jello ring and mold and chill until firm, 2 hours.

title: blueberry yogurt pancakes
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Beat egg with yogurt and milk in a large bowl.
Beat in oil, then add flour mixture. Stir just until combined.
(Batter can be a little lumpy.)

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add mashed beans.
Add hot ketchup; simmer. Top with cheese.
Serve with nachos.

title: baklava
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 300°.
In large bowl mix walnuts, sugar and cinnamon.
In pan, place 1 sheet of phyllo, allowing it to extend up sides; brush with butter.
Repeat to make 5 layers.
Sprinkle with 1 cup nut mixture.
Cut remaining phyllo into approximately 13 x 9-inch rectangles.
Place a sheet of phyllo in pan; brush with butter.
Repeat to make 6 layers, overlapping phyllo if necessary to make rectangle.
Top with 1 cup nut mixture. Repeat.
End with phyllo on top.
Trim overhang.
Using a sharp knife cut halfway through all layers in a diamond pattern to make 24 servings.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes or until top is brown.

title: microwave croutons
directions: Place butter in a 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Microwave on High for 35 seconds or until melted.
Stir in salad seasoning. Add bread cubes. Stir gently to coat.
Microwave on High 4 1/2 to 5 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times. Cool.
(Croutons will crisp as they cool.)
Store croutons in an airtight container.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix all ingredients together. Heat in a shallow pan at 350 degrees until hot and bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: crab delight
directions: Boil rice and put in 11 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cut crab into bite size pieces and spread over rice.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: In small bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and Blue Bonnet until blended.
Spread 1/2 mixture on ham slice.
Roll up. Chill for several hours or freeze.
Slice and serve on crackers.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and oleo.
Add sugar and beat well.
In another bowl, beat eggs and add milk to eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with eggs and milk to butter and sugar.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Be sure to use a large tube pan that has been greased and floured.

title: spanish rice
directions: Place oil in medium skillet that has a tight-fitting lid. Heat about 2 minutes on medium-high.
Add rice and brown about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: raspberry trifle
directions: Make vanilla pudding according to directions and fold in raspberries.
Place in refrigerator to partially set.
Line 11 x 7 x 2-inch glass dish with ladyfingers, split open.
Spoon over a layer of vanilla pudding, then a layer of raspberry Jell-O mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.
May be made a day ahead of time.

title: peach cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange half the slices on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large mixer bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, water and extract; mix well.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: miss mae's lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion (drain).
Add all ingredients (except cheeses) and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Grease 2 rectangular bakers or one very large pan.
Layer sauce, noodles, sauce, cheese, noodles, sauce and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. May be frozen before baking.

title: maria's pumpkin bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, water, oil and pumpkin; stir until blended.
Add nuts.
Pour mixture into 3 greased bread pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool slightly in pans.
Turn out on rack to finish cooling.
Flavor is best if baked a day before using.
Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: instant peach pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, milk, sour cream and almond extract in bowl.
Beat 1 minute with wire whisk.
Pour into pie shell.
Let sit until filling is set.
Arrange peach slices on top of pie.
In a small saucepan, heat preserves and water; stirring until mixture begins to bubble.
Cool slightly and spoon over peaches. Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: ginger-bake sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange the potato slices in an overlapping pattern in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In a small bowl, combine the apple juice, ginger root and honey or brown sugar; and pour the mixture over the potatoes.
Bake at 425° until potatoes have a golden tinge and the liquid has been absorbed, 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: almond roca
directions: Put half of the almonds in the bottom of a shallow cookie sheet with sides.
Add half the grated chocolate bar.
Stirring constantly, cook butter and sugar to 300° on candy thermometer. Stir in vanilla. Pour over nuts and chocolate.
Top with balance of chocolate and rest of nuts.
Cool completely and break into pieces.
Store in cool place.

title: zucchini tea bread
directions: On wax paper, mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat together eggs, oil, honey and vanilla in large bowl.
Stir in zucchini.
Gradually stir in flour mixture, keeping smooth.
Stir in walnuts.

title: everyday cupcakes
directions: Stir shortening just to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 the milk and egg.
Mix until all flour is dampened, then beat vigorously 2 minutes.
Add rest of milk and vanilla; beat 1 minute. Fill paper-lined cupcake pans 1/2 full.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 18 to 20.

title: green rice bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Saute onion in butter; stir in rice, soup and broccoli.
Turn into shallow, buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Blend in powdered sugar.
Add oleo and blend until crumbly.
Add orange juice.
Roll into balls; then roll in coconut.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Add grated nuts, if desired, before rolling into balls.
Makes 30.

title: homemade pancake syrup
directions: Mix and boil until thick.
Great over pancakes or French toast.

title: chicken and noodles(country:  u. s. a.)
directions: Remove fat from chicken; cut into cubes.
Saute with onion and soy sauce.
Cook on high for 8 to 10 minutes; then cook on low for 45 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add more soy sauce to taste.
Serve over buttered noodles.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover; chill overnight before serving.

title: lush
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and pecans.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with the mixture.
Bake in conventional oven 25 minutes or in microwave for 7 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together.
Spread on first layer. Beat Jell-O pudding and milk together and pour on second layer. Top with a layer of Cool Whip and sprinkle a few pecans on top.

title: 7 layer squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch glass baking pan.
Place apple slices in the pan.
Mix the butter and sugar together and add the rest of the ingredients; mixture will be coarse.
Sprinkle over the apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until the apples are tender and the topping is golden brown in a 375° oven.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine the ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat until thickened.

title: ham puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to a rolling boil in a 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour and stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball (about one minute).
Beat in the eggs (4) all at once until smooth and glossy.
Drop dough by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until puffed, golden brown and dry, about 25 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: Spray electric frying pan with Pam.
Brown chicken on all sides for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add mushrooms, carrots, water, rice, onion, bouillon, poultry seasoning and salt.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: cheesy baked asparagus
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine asparagus, cheese and 1/4 cup butter.
Spoon mixture into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.

title: hot or cold pasta shell tuna salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain tuna.
In a large bowl, mix together the pasta, tuna, tomatoes, olives and onion, then the cubed meat last.
Add the salad dressing according to taste.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese (if desired).
Great for parties, lunch or a light dinner.
You can add celery or green peppers, whatever you like!
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Make Jell-O; add cranberries and stir until cranberries are mixed well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chewy and soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Slowly add instant pudding, mixing very well.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop teaspoonful on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° (preheated oven) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies will appear light in color.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Put in large pan (Dutch oven) with enough water just to cover.
Cut up onion and add.
Let cook until potatoes are soft.
Add basil, salt and pepper while cooking. After potatoes have cooked almost all the way, add butter or margarine.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given. Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 minutes.

title: egg and cheese casserole
directions: Mix bread cubes with melted margarine.
Line bottom of 8 x 13-inch casserole with bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs and milk until fluffy.
Add mustard and cayenne pepper.
Salt and pepper may be added.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Great and easy for brunch!

title: tomato phyllo pizza
directions: Brush a baking sheet lightly with some of the butter.
Lay 1 sheet of the phyllo on the butter and brush it lightly with some of the remaining butter.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of Parmesan. Lay another sheet of phyllo on top and press firmly so it adheres to bottom layer.
Butter, sprinkle and layer remaining phyllo in the same manner, ending with a sheet of phyllo and reserving 1 tablespoon Parmesan.
Sprinkle top with Mozzarella; scatter onion evenly and arrange tomato slices over onion.
Sprinkle pizza with Parmesan, oregano, thyme, salt and pepper.
Bake in middle of preheated 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or edges are golden.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter in saucepan; bring to rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add cocoa, oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Makes 24.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown diced onion in shortening.
Add ground beef and brown. Add all other ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes enough for 16 buns.

title: colonial sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender or two knives.
Add sweet potatoes and enough milk to make a soft (not wet) dough.
Knead lightly. Roll dough into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds or squares. Place on lightly oiled baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until lightly brown.
Makes 12 medium biscuits.

title: mother's cinnamon pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and simmer in 2-quart heavy saucepan until mixture threads when dropped from a spoon or forms a soft ball in cold water (15 to 20 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in pecans.
Continue stirring until all nuts are sugar coated and break into original halves.
Will last forever in plastic bags or tightly covered containers.

title: three layer cookies
directions: Line lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan with crackers (single layer).
Bring sugars, graham crackers, milk and margarine to a boil, stirring occasionally, so it doesn't burn.
Boil slowly for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Shred cheeses.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, bean dip and taco seasoning and whip together. Alternate layers of dip and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Dip with corn chips.

title: squash crescents
directions: Bring milk to boil, add shortening, sugar, salt and squash. Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water, after 5 minutes, add to milk mixture.
Add 1 c. flour and beaten egg, beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Mix well.
Cover dough and let rise in warm place about 1 1/2 hours or until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut and shape into rolls. Place on greased baking sheet and brush with melted butter.
Let rise about 1/2 hour.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine fresh vegetables, cheese cubes and noodles.
Add dressing and toss well. Chill before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes well; mix in pineapple (undrained).
Add orange juice to moisten; spread in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and a little nutmeg.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: volcano potatoes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes as you normally do.
Place potatoes in casserole dish.
Make a well in center of the potatoes.
Take whipped cream (whip as directed on carton) and cheese.
Fold into the whipped cream and spoon into the well.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Will run over top of the potatoes.

title: pat's venison pot roast
directions: Put all ingredients in large pressure cooker.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour.

title: eggplant companato
directions: Saute the eggplant in 1/2 cup olive oil; add the sliced onion, celery and garlic, then add the tomato sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Cool to mellow flavors.
This freezes well and is great on sandwiches or as a side condiment.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add vanilla.
Alternate sifted flour and water.
Fold
in pecans.
Shape into balls and bake at 325° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: onion casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Use Pyrex or other 8 x 8-inch dish.

title: gelatin sundaes
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Spoon ice cream and gelatin alternately into tall sundae dishes, ending with gelatin and filling to within 1/2-inch of top of dish.
Top with whipped topping and nuts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Put potatoes in a large pan with just enough water to cover. Add onions and bouillon.
Cook until tender.
Mash mixture with a potato masher (non-electric).
Add cheese and let it melt.
Then add milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: breakfast bar
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients (mixture will be dry).
Add raisins. Add oatmeal or rice cereal.
To mixture, add cold water, enough to make dry paste.
Form into bars on waxed paper; refrigerate (can be frozen).
One breakfast bar equals 1 protein (meat), 1 milk, 1 fat, 1 fruit and 1 bread.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine like cookie dough.
With hands, press in bottom of an 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate fudge with cherries
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring gently.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add chocolate pieces, marshmallow cream, nuts and cherries.
Stir until blended thoroughly.
Pour into two large pans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: beat 'n eat icing
directions: Mix in a small bowl.
Add boiling water and beat well until stiff.
The recipe makes a fluffy icing that will stay moist for 2 or 3 days.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring thoroughly.
Sift together rest of ingredients and mix with other ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Stir in dry ingredients and stir until dough is stiff.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Make meatballs by cooking until brown the first 7 mixed ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes or bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain fat from meatballs; do not use.
Mix brown sugar and cornstarch in skillet.
Stir in pineapple (with syrup), vinegar and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Add meatballs.
Cover; simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Stir in green pepper.
Cover; simmer until crisp-tender, 5 minutes.

title: strawberry sensation
directions: Cake:
Mix, bake and cool cake as directed on the package, using the lite recipe and adding 1 cup La Creme.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: strawberry sparkle cake
directions: Bake angel food cake as directed on back of package and cool. Dissolve gelatin in water and add frozen block of strawberries, stirring to break up and mix berries.
Place cake, widest side down, on a serving plate.
Cut a 1-inch layer from the top and set aside.
Cut around cake 1 inch from outer edge to 1 inch from bottom.
Then cut around cake 1 inch from inner edge to 1 inch from bottom.
Gently remove the section of cake between cuts, tearing it into small pieces.
Fold pieces into strawberry mixture, and pour into cake shell.
Place cake layer on top.

title: gabby's red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco and sugar together, add eggs, coloring, cocoa and salt.
Add buttermilk, flour and vanilla gradually.
Fold in vinegar and soda mixture.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: date bars
directions: Mix together the margarine, oatmeal, soda in hot water, brown sugar and flour.
Press one layer of dough on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Boil together the water, sugar, dates and chopped nuts until thickened.
Cool and spread thinly over layer of dough in the pan.
Press on another layer of dough. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: foolproof homemade yogurt
directions: Use glass or ceramic container with loose-fitting cover, never plastic or metal.

title: lemon chicken
directions: In paper or plastic bag, combine flour, salt and paprika. Brush chicken with lemon juice.
Add 2 to 3 pieces of chicken at a time to bag and shake well.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in hot Crisco.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 3/4 cup boiling water; pour over chicken.
Stir in onion, brown sugar, peel and remaining lemon juice.
Cover: reduce heat.

title: apple plus
directions: Cream butter and margarine.
Add sugar and blend well.
Beat in eggs.
Mix in vanilla and flour (that has been sifted with soda and salt).
Add apples, pecans, coconut and dates.
Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 1 hour at 300°, then 25 minutes at 325°. Test to see if it is done.

title: meringue frosting
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Bring slowly to a boil, then boil rapidly to 236°, the soft ball stage. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup very slowly over egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and continue beating until frosting holds its shape.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet.
Add all other ingredients and simmer.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch together.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip or meringue.
You can also cook in microwave.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush crackers until fine. Cream butter and sugar, add eggs. Then add crackers and other ingredients except nuts. Mix, then add nuts. Grease tube pan and line with wax paper. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours. Turn oven off but leave cake in hot oven for 1/2 hour.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
To serve add 3 tablespoons per cup of hot water.
Add marshmallows if desired.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground meat and onions in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs and baking mix until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: minted fruit salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except fruit; stir until sugar dissolves.
Place fruit in large, shallow dish; pour ReaLemon brand mixture over.
Cover; chill 3 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mini pizza
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, garlic and oregano.
Heat to blend flavors.
Spread on muffins; top with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Makes 8 mini pizzas.

title: holiday pineapple cheese ball
directions: Add green peppers, onion, pineapple, salt and 1 cup pecans to softened cream cheese; mix well.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with crackers or fresh fruit.

title: black bean tamale pie
directions: Delicious on a cold winter's day and even better the next!

title: gooey dessert
directions: Bake until lightly browned (burns easily).

title: tangy beans
directions: Defrost green beans in mushroom sauce by boiling 12 minutes. Combine mustard, sugar, margarine and seasonings; heat.
Add lemon juice and vinegar and stir smooth.
Pour over beans and heat through before serving.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the chocolate chips. Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread melted chocolate chips over mixture.
Refrigerate until firm. Warm slightly at room temperature and cut into squares.
Makes 4 dozen squares.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer.
Bake at 350° in a greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(Check for doneness after 1 hour.)
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, saute onions and celery in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Brown about 10 minutes, then stir in chili beans, refried beans, corn and taco sauce. Place 1/2 of the tortillas in a 10-inch square baking dish; top with cheese.
Bake covered until cheese is melted.
Garnish with fresh whole chili peppers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (350° if using glass pans).
Cream butter and
cup
of	sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, salt
and baking powder together and stir into butter-sugar mixture.
Alternate with milk.
Beat until smooth.	Pour into
a 2-quart buttered casserole.
Spoon drained fruit over batter. Sprinkle
to 1/2 cup sugar over fruit, depending on sweetness
of
fruit.
Pour 1 cup of fruit juice over top. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until top springs back when lightly touched. Serve plain or with cream.

title: ore-ida o'brien cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs mixed with oleo and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in pan over low heat.
Let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg and beat well.
Add flour, baking soda, cloves and ginger.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add buttermilk, soda and water. Add flavoring then add eggs, one at a time, then add flour last. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: corned beef and cabbage(crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients EXCEPT cabbage wedges in Crock-Pot in the order listed.
Cover and cook on Low 8-10 hours (High:
5-6 hours).
Add cabbage wedges to liquid, pushing down to moisten, turn to High and cook an additional 2-3 hours.
If you want more cabbage than the Crock-Pot can hold, cook it separately in a skillet.
Just remove 1 c. of broth from Crock-Pot during the last hour of cooking and pour it over cabbage wedges in the skillet. Cover and cook slowly for 20-30 minutes.

title: lime cheesecake
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix with margarine.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water. Blend in cream cheese.
Cool.
Chill evaporated milk, bowl and beaters until icy cold.
Whip milk and add to jello mixture.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Chill firm, at least 4 hours.

title: icebox dessert
directions: Prepare all puddings in Pyrex bowl.
Layer chocolate, graham cookies, vanilla and cookies, then butterscotch and cookies.
Top with Cool Whip.
Put into freezer.
Take out 30 minutes before you want to use so that it will be easy to cut out.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and chop.
Cook rice.
Saute onion in the margarine,
Combine all ingredients and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Punch holes in cake while hot.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and caramel sauce over cake.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip, then break up Heath bars and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: tortilla roll-up
directions: Spread cream cheese on 1/2 of each tortilla.
Add thin slices of each kind of meat.
Spread with small amounts of dill dip and mustard.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add lettuce leaves and roll into a tight roll.
May be rolled in paper towels and refrigerated or serve immediately.
Makes great picnic sandwiches.

title: spicy cake
directions: Sift and mix dry ingredients.
Add moist ingredients.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Ideal with French vanilla icing, then sprinkled with cinnamon.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Tip:
You can pound chicken breasts flat and leave flattened between sheets of plastic wrap.
Wrap them airtight in one package and freeze for later use.

title: tiger meat
directions: Tell the butcher to grind the round or chuck for tiger meat and do not season.
Combine all the ingredients together.
Mix well and roll into "ball like" meat loaf.
Wrap in plastic wrap, then foil.
Let stand in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours.

title: country captain fried chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour seasoned with salt and pepper; shake off excess.
Heat oil and butter in a heavy skillet large enough to hold chicken in one layer or cook in batches.
Brown chicken on all sides and remove from pan.
To the skillet add onion, garlic, peppers, mushrooms, raisins, curry powder and thyme, stirring until vegetables are wilted.
Add tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil, stirring and add chicken pieces, skin side up.
Cover and cook until chicken is cooked thoroughly, about 30 minutes.
Serve with cooked rice, toasted almonds and chutney on the side.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix milk, flour and cracked eggs in a bowl.
Then add margarine and mashed strawberries to mixture.
Also, add sugar, salt, baking powder and food coloring to mixture.
Stir with a spoon.
Pour into cake pan.
Put in oven and bake for 10 minutes in the oven on low temperature about 70°.
Take it out to cool when done.
Put strawberry icing on cake.
Then eat it.
It will serve about 20 people.

title: campbelled eggs
directions: In bowl,
stir	soup
until
smooth; gradually blend in eggs and pepper.
In 10-inch skillet, melt butter; pour in egg mixture. Cook
over low heat; do not stir.	As mixture begins to set around
edges,
gently lift cooked portions with large turner so that
uncooked
portion
can
flow	to
the bottom. Continue gently
lifting
cooked
portions until eggs are completely set, but
still	moist
(about
minutes).
Makes 4 servings.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Note: May add or take away any veggies.

title: chinese coleslaw(very good!)
directions: Combine coleslaw mixture, almonds and green onions in large bowl.
Sprinkle uncooked broken Ramen noodles, reserving seasoning packets.
Combine sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper and seasoning packets in small bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon over salad and toss to coat.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fresh berry soup(yields 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Combine any combination of yogurt, buttermilk or sour cream to make 4 cups.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning together and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread sour cream over beans and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Boil ribs with an onion, speared, and whole garlic cloves for 1 hour.
Place boiled ribs in a shallow baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients (except rice); pour over ribs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Great with a green salad and corn.

title: christmas punch
directions: Blend juices and sugar; chill.
Yields approximately 1 quart liquid.
Add sherbet and Sprite just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: instant protein candy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add granola until mixture is stiff. Knead like bread dough.
Form into small logs or balls and roll into chopped nuts.
Refrigerate and cut in bite size pieces.

title: corn pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in 9-inch pie shell.
Top with crust (make a vent for steam to escape).
Use a pie
crust for 2-layer, 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blest french toast
directions: Mix together eggs, milk, syrup and cinnamon.
Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Layer 1/2 of bread, all of cream cheese, then rest of bread.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let cool slightly; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve with maple syrup and butter. Try adding apples and/or raisins, even coconut.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir some of the hot milk mixture into beaten eggs; mix well. Return egg mixture to saucepan.
Heat to boiling, boil 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat 1/2 cup heavy cream until soft peaks form.
Fold into custard.
Spread 1 cup of custard mixture into prepared pie shell.
Slice 2 bananas.
Arrange over the custard.
Pour remaining custard over bananas.
Whip remaining 1/2 cup heavy cream.
Using a filled pastry bag with a decorative tip, pipe cream around edge and in center of pie.
Chill 2 to 3 hours until firm.
Just before serving, slice remaining banana and garnish top of pie.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook diced celery until tender; drain.
Make white sauce from milk and liquid drained from celery, butter, flour and salt.
Melt butter in pan; add bread which has been shredded in small pieces. Stir until coated with butter.
Mix celery with white sauce.
Put in greased casserole and sprinkle buttered bread on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly and brown.
Serves 6.

title: red raspberry jello
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add applesauce and raspberries and juice.
Let set up in refrigerator.
Garnish with the sour cream and marshmallows mixed together; spread on top.

title: lasagna
directions: Sauce:
Brown meat in oil.
Add diced onion, tomato paste, water, parsley, salt, pepper and bay leaves.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Arrange in large baking dish in layers as follows:
sauce, noodles, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes, or until cheese on top is melted.

title: sunday morning sausage ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter a 9-inch ring mold.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Pack into mold and bake 20 minutes.
Take from oven and pour off any excess fat.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Turn onto heated platter and fill center with scrambled eggs (8 to 12 eggs).

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Put oil in frypan on medium heat (or wok if you have one). Add rice, onion, egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and cook long enough for onion to be tender.
Add more Worcestershire to taste if needed.
Don't overcook.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add oil and eggs and beat. Add carrots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 13 x 9 1/4 x 2-inch cake pan.

title: granny's banana pudding
directions: In skillet, stir sugar and flour together until well blended. Stir in milk, vanilla, butter and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat until thick like pudding.
Pour over cut bananas and vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough, or just scrub and rinse them. Cut potatoes into thin slices (not all the way through).
Tip: Use a handle of a wooden spoon to keep knife from cutting all the way.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups chicken broth.
Combine all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: meat loaf delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into loaf pan.
Pat meat mixture down.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Occasionally drain off excess fat.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: You may use 2 pints canned yellow squash, drained.

title: soy fried rice
directions: Heat oil.
Add eggs, mixing constantly while breaking up with a fork.
Add eggs and onions to rice with soy sauce to color rice brown.
Add diced shrimp or pork.
Blend very well and serve hot.

title: red shell noodle salad
directions: Cook shell noodles (firm, not soft).
Drain.
Rinse in warm to cool water.
Add some Russian, Western and French dressings to moisten.
Add basil, parsley and a pinch of Mrs. Dash to taste; celery seed is optional.
Add more dressing if needed.
Cool a few hours or overnight.
Stir and add a bit more dressing, if needed. Stir before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
From into marble-sized balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in covered container.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Drain artichoke hearts and mash well with a fork.
Do not use blender.
Add mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.

Mix together and spread into a baking dish large enough to spread the mixture to about 1/2-inch thick. Sprinkle top with paprika and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Serve with crackers of any variety.
Makes 2 cups.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together (save 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup French fried onions).
Pour in casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: fruitful harvest tzimmes
directions: Lay alternate layers of sweet potatoes, apple slices, raisins and pecans in a lightly oiled 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine honey, oil, orange peel, salt, cinnamon and ginger.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry pie jello
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add cherry pie filling.
Mix well and chill until firm.
Drain pineapple and mix well with cream cheese. Spread over jello mixture and chill.

title: ginger pear salad
directions: Mash cream cheese and Jell-O (dry) until smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir until smooth.
Add ginger to juice and allow to dissolve.
Add Miracle Whip.
Beat until smooth.
Add pear juice and ice cubes.
When thickened, add pears and pecan pieces. Serves 12.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Add egg and vanilla. Alternate dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in chips. Drop dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Shape into pumpkin shape. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Decorate with icing or peanut butter.
Use candy, nuts or raisins to form face.
Makes 19 to 20 large cookies.

title: molasses popcorn balls
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Boil until brittle when dropped in cold water.
Pour over 3 quarts of popcorn.
Press into balls.

title: western skillet
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat, stirring frequently.
Stir in soup mixture, water, rice and tomatoes and peas.
Bring to a boil. Simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes until rice is tender.
Top with cheese.

title: prairie rice dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Saute bell pepper and onion.
Add all other ingredients, except sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Add sour cream just before serving.
Serve as a dip or as a main dish over extra rice.

title: zesty zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in zucchini, onion and carrots. In separate bowl combine stuffing mix and butter. Spread half of stuffing mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon vegetable mixture over top, then layer of cheese.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond squash
directions: Bring squash to a boil in water; cook covered until tender. Drain. Saute onion in butter until tender.	 Add flour, salt, pepper, oregano, sour cream and almonds. Heat thoroughly. Pour over
squash; mix well. Pour into casserole. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add parsley or chives before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Grease stem pan; sprinkle with 1/2 cup of pecans.
Pour in cake and bake in preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Leave cake in pan when removed from oven!

title: old fashioned sauerkraut
directions: Chop bacon and fry.
Add chopped onion and saute.
Add flour and brown lightly.
Add sauerkraut, caraway seed and water.
Stir well and cook until thickened.
Good served with sausage and potatoes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place rolls in pizza pan or jelly roll pan and bake according to package directions; let cool.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and milk until soft ball stage is reached.
Add chocolate pieces and marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add nuts.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour in large dish and cut into squares.

title: sweet kraut salad
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and let sit in refrigerator for a few hours.
Serve cold.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Cool until consistency of egg whites.
Add fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: pasta with broccoli and garbanzo beans
directions: To start this meal right, prepare an easy-to-assemble platter of purchased caponata (eggplant relish), Italian olives, roasted peppers and seeded breadsticks.
Finish up dinner by drizzling sliced oranges with some Grand Marnier.

title: csirkepaprikas(chicken paprika)
directions: Sprinkle salt over chicken; let stand for a half hour.
Saute onions and garlic in vegetable oil until golden.
Add black pepper and the paprikas; stir (don't let paprika burn).
Add water.
Add chicken and cook until tender, approximately 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix the food coloring and cocoa together and set aside.
Mix the Crisco and sugar together well. Add eggs and cocoa mixture to batter, then buttermilk.
Lastly add the flour, salt and vanilla. Beat it well. Remove from mixer and add the vinegar and baking soda mixture last, beating this portion by hand into the cake mixture.
Bake in well-greased and floured loaf or layer pans for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven. When cooled, frost with any icing.
Buttercream icing is excellent with this cake.

title: sunbeam chocolate cake
directions: All ingredients at room temperature.
Sift flour, soda, salt, and cocoa together.
Cream oleo and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Bake in three cake pans (3 layers) 325°.

title: carrot salad(can be made a day ahead)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except lettuce, in a glass or plastic bowl.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours or until chilled. Serve on lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.
One serving has 50 calories.

title: gingerbread with sauce
directions: Bake as directed on box.

title: fruit salad pudding
directions: Combine all
ingredients.
Do not drain the fruit.
Use the pudding mix dry.
Refrigerate 1 hour before using.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cheese and potatoes.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a 2-quart casserole for about 45 minutes.
Put butter and chives on top.

title: banana coffee bread
directions: Cooks Note:
Bananas must be over ripe.
Do not use a blender or food processor to mash bananas, as it almost liquefies them.

title: hearty baked beans
directions: Cut bacon crosswise into 1/4-inch wide strips. Place in a nonstick skillet.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until crisp, stirring occasionally.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Combine onion mixture, beans and next 6 ingredients.
Spoon into a 2-quart baking dish, coated with cooking spray.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 10 servings.

title: reduced calorie raspberry filled muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners. In bowl, using electric mixer, cream margarine with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add milk, egg and extract; beat until combined. Combine flour, baking powder and stir into margarine mixture. Fill each muffin cup with equal amounts of batter.
Using bottom of 1 teaspoon measure make indentation in top of each muffin. Fill each indentation with 1 teaspoon raspberry spread.
Bake 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pan and cool.
Makes 12 muffins, 120 calories each.

title: cierra's cupcakes
directions: Stir up the eggs.
Put in mix, butter and sugar.
Stir it more.
Put in cupcake papers in the pans.
Bake in oven.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars, margarine and oil.
Beat well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Stir in soda, cream of tartar, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Form small balls (large hickory nut size) and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork or the bottom of a glass.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until slightly brown.
Makes lots of cookies that melt in your mouth!

title: prune cake with icing
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add dry ingredients, vanilla, nuts, prunes and buttermilk.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes in oblong pan.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients good.
Chill for one hour.
Serve as a dip on fruit or cake cubes.
Good as a topping for fruit salad.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Combine flour and salt.
Add dry ingredients and chocolate syrup to creamed mixture.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Pour into a greased and floured (Baker's Joy) 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Mix cake and pudding together and spread on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with chopped walnuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 to 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Batter will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Yields 60 muffins.

title: caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Alternately add flour mixture and sour cream to butter mixture. Add vanilla. Grease and lightly flour 6 (9-inch) pans. Pour in batter and bake 25 to 35 minutes or until done. Remove from oven and cool on racks for 10 minutes. Cool cake completely before frosting.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and vanilla.
Combine flour, pecans and salt.
Stir into butter mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cool, then roll again.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook on High for 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla and cook on High for 2 minutes longer.
Add soda and quickly stir until light and foamy. Immediately pour into greased baking sheet.
Quickly spread out thin.
When cool, break into pieces.
Store in a tight container. Makes 1 pound.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Before starting, bring cream cheese to room temperature. Heat liquid from oranges and pineapple with water in a medium sauce pan. Bring to boil, then add jello and sugar. Stir until dissolved well. In a large mixing bowl combine mixture, fruit,
cool whip, and cream cheese. Mix well and pour into large glass baking dish. Refrigerate one hour and serve.

title: coconut date cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs and then add dates. Heat in saucepan until dates dissolve, then cook 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add flavoring, nuts and cereal.
Form balls and roll in the coconut.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; add to creamed mixture. Stir in milk, vanilla, and walnuts. Beat egg whites with cream of tartar; fold into above mixture. Bake at 350° in two 9-inch round cake pans.

title: peanut butter yums yums
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix together.
Add to the mixture 1 package of oyster crackers. Mix together and place on paper towel to absorb any extra juice.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash and trim okra, leaving
a	little	of stem.
Place garlic and pepper in bottom
of
sterilized
jars.
Pack
okra firmly in jars.
Add dill seed.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil. Simmer 15 minutes.	Pour over okra.
Seal in jars. Let stand 7 to 9 weeks.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter over low heat, then add sugar.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Pour into shell and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine onion flakes and vinegar; let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables.

title: pork chops with orange sauce
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in a frying pan with a little oil.
Take pork chops out of frying pan.
Add all other ingredients and mix together.
Put pork chops back in frying pan and cover.
Simmer until done.

title: tostados
directions: Crumble and brown sausage.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons fat. Fry beans, add sausage, seasonings and mix.
Lay tortillas on pan. Spread with sausage mix.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: mocha fudge pie
directions: Combine hot water and 2 teaspoons coffee in mixing bowl; stir well.
Add brownie mix, 1 teaspoon vanilla and egg whites; stir until well blended.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 22 minutes.
Let crust cool completely.

title: sugar-free cake
directions: Cook raisins and water together until tender in covered pan. Cut up dates.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of pan.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, salt and soda.
Add dates and shortening to hot raisins and stir until blended.
Add the applesauce, vanilla and sweetener.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: allison's chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt caramels and 1/3 cup Pet milk in microwave. Mix together box of cake mix, 3/4 cup melted butter, 1 cup chopped pecans and 1/3 cup Pet milk. Put 1/2 of the cake mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 6 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with 6 ounces of chocolate chips and drizzle the caramel mixture over it. Crumble the remaining dough on top of this or it may be easier to roll out the remaining dough between two sheets of waxed paper and then "lift" the dough on top of the chips/caramel mixture. Bake for 18 minutes. Let cool completely before cutting.

title: calabasa(mexican stew)
directions: Boil cubed pork in lightly salted water for about 30 minutes. Drain.
Add canned tomatoes, squash and onion; simmer until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add cumin, salt and pepper to taste.
(Can serve with warmed tortillas or rice.)

title: vegetable bake
directions: Slice onions, potatoes and squash and quarter cabbage.
On large double sheets of Reynolds Wrap, place vegetables.
Slice butter on top of vegetables and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake in oven at 350° until tender or bake on grill while cooking out or place in hot coals of open fire.

title: roquefort log
directions: Combine cheeses.
Blend in next four ingredients.
Chill. Shape in a roll 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Coat with nuts.
Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice and serve with crackers.
Makes about 1 cup spread.

title: quick creamy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, heat butter until just melted; remove from heat.
Add cocoa and whisk until blended. Next, stir in sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, stirring quickly because batter will be warm.
Gently stir in flour and nuts.
Add vanilla last.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch square pan with with the cooking spray oil.	Pour batter into pan.
Sprinkle a few additional nuts on top of batter for a pretty effect.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes (until center is just cooked).

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Melt both sticks of butter with the sugar.
Boil 2 minutes. Coat graham crackers with mixture and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add molasses and egg.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add rice, onions, mushrooms and almonds.
Saute until
rice
lightens
in color, about 10 minutes. Place in
covered casserole dish and add chicken broth. Place in 350°
oven	and
bake,
covered,
for
1 hour.
There probably will be some liquid left.
This dish sits well and is great for parties and also good reheated.

title: smoked turkey ball
directions: With mixer or food processor, blend turkey, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans and parsley.
Serve with Triscuits.
Must be prepared ahead.
Serves 12.

title: holiday yum yum cake
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients.
Mix flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Sift and mix with boiled mixture.
Pour into two small bread loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Or for a large cake, pour into regular sized bread loaf pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
When cool, frost with white buttercream icing.
Decorate with nuts and candied fruit.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together in blender.
Chill and serve with fresh fruit.

title: chicken ravioli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with grated cheese and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Use broth from cooked chicken and thicken as for gravy.
Salt to taste.
Pour over mixture and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in small pan.
Add water and cook low until thick.

title: scalloped cauliflower
directions: Break
the
cauliflower
into flowerets before boiling. Drain. Place
a
layer of the cooked cauliflower in a greased baking dish.
Add
a
layer of egg slices or of grated cheese, then a layer of white sauce.
Repeat until all the cauliflower is used. Put
a
layer of buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake in a moderate oven
at
to 400° for 15 to 30 minutes.
A bit of cayenne pepper
or paprika may be added for additional seasoning.

title: mexican vegetarian pasta
directions: Place a large pot of water over high heat and bring to a boil. In the meantime, heat oil in skillet, add garlic and saut briefly.
Add zucchini, yellow squash, bell pepper and corn; quickly stir-fry.
Add beans and salsa and heat through.

title: rice gruel(lugaw)
directions: Clean chicken well.
Wash rice and drain.
Boil water.
Add patis, rice and chicken.
Boil on medium-high heat.
Cook until soft.
Fry garlic, onion and ginger in a large pot.
Pour in rice mixture.
Add salt to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples and mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° until cake shrinks from edge of pan (over 1 hour).

title: brisket
directions: Place brisket in flat pan which is lined with heavy foil. Combine ingredients and pour over brisket.
Fold foil over and seal tightly.
Tenderize overnight.
When ready to cook, bake 45 minutes per pound at 350°.
(Check meat for doneness; if overdone, it will fall apart.)
Can cool and refrigerate.
Slice with electric knife:
thin for sandwiches, thicker with barbecue sauce. Can use juices for au jus or gravy.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Spread coconut on bottom.
Spread pecans on top of coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour over nuts and coconut.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure.
Add baking powder, salt, granulated sugar and 1 tablespoon cocoa and sift again.
Add milk, shortening and vanilla.
Mix only until smooth, then add nuts. Pour into greased casserole or small baking dish.
Mix together brown sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle over batter, then pour boiling water over top of the batter.
(This makes a chocolate sauce in the bottom of pan after pudding is baked.) Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rocky road
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips and butter.
Add the milk; stir.
Add the marshmallows and peanuts.
Stir to coat. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been lined with wax paper. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Remove Rocky Road from pan and cut into small squares.

title: cool squash salad
directions: Into a large salad bowl, slice all ingredients and toss with your favorite salad dressing.
May be served garnished with slices or quarters of boiled egg and black olives.

title: mom's broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
Place in drainer and let stand. Saute onion in butter, then add soup and milk.
Mix together, then add Cheez Whiz.
Mix until creamy.
Take off heat and stir in rice and broccoli.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown on top.

title: simple biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick; cut into biscuits with anything round or with cookie cutters.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: polish cookies(chrusciki)
directions: Combine sour cream and egg yolks.
Blend in flour to make a soft dough; knead until combined.
Roll out, using flour to prevent sticking, until thin.
Cut into strips about 1 inch wide. About every 2 inches, cut on a diagonal to make diamond shapes. Make slit in center of each; push one end through to make a bow tie.
Fry in hot fat until brown.
Drain and cool; sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix (less 1 cup), 1 egg and 1 stick melted butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and flatten.
Mix the pumpkin pie mix, 2 eggs and milk.
Pour over first layer.
Mix and sprinkle remaining ingredients on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Best served warm.

title: no egg chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add milk. Add butter and vanilla last.

title: dill french green beans
directions: Saute French-style green beans in butter.
Add lemon juice, dill weed and garlic salt.
Mix well and heat.
Add cherry tomato halves and sliced black olives.
Heat a few minutes and serve. Serves 5.

title: chocolate-dipped heart cookies
directions: You will need a heart shaped cookie cutter.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Layer beans in a 9 x 13-inch or smaller glass pan.
Spread avocado dip on top of beans.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning mix together and spread mixture on top of avocado dip.
Layer olives on top of sour cream and top off with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: zesty italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into a cake pan or casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crystal's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter flavor Crisco, Crisco, brown sugar, sugar, milk, vanilla and eggs until creamy.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Place oats in blender until coarse powder.
Gradually add to mixture.
Blend well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by tablespoons on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool on baking sheet for 2 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into a shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and onions, bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix altogether; mold or shape into ball. Serve with crackers or Melba toast.

title: swiss steak supreme
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces and coat with flour.
Melt margarine in pan and brown meat on both sides.
Add tomatoes, salt, basil and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour until tender.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook another 25 minutes.
Top with cheese until it melts.

title: crackle
directions: Melt butter and sugar in a saucepan together about 10 minutes on low until white, thick and bubbly.
Line a cookie sheet pan with crackers.
Pour mixture over evenly.
Spread over crackers thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes, until golden tan and bubbly.
Take out of oven and sprinkle chocolate bits over and smooth.
Top with optional nuts or candy sprinkles.
Refrigerate for several hours until hardened and then "crack" the pan.

title: lettuce-english pea salad
directions: Combine vegetable oil through oregano in a jar and shake well (makes dressing).

title: lace cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add beaten egg, oatmeal, brown sugar, vanilla, salt and almonds.
Drop by one-half teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet with plenty of room because they spread.
Bake about 6 minutes at 375°.
Let cool about 1 minute on sheet.
Then remove quickly and roll in powdered sugar.
Very fragile and best to bake only one sheet at a time.
Dough can be refrigerated or frozen and used in parts.
Makes about 11 dozen.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and beat again.
Add remaining ingredients and beat again.

title: tokyo turkey toss
directions: In a large bowl, combine all but the mayonnaise and the almonds.
Mix well and chill.
Just before serving, add mayonnaise and toasted almonds.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: nut-a-roohs
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and peanut butter.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Pour over rest of ingredients and mix well.
Press into large oblong cake pan.

title: microwave peppermint candy
directions: Chunk up the almond bark into pieces.
Put the pieces into a 2 quart bowl and microwave, stirring occasionally, for about 3 minutes.
Now pound up the candy canes into fine granular state. Mix the fine peppermint into the melted almond bark and spread out on wax paper to cool.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: blackened redfish
directions: Heat a large cast-iron skillet over very high heat until it is beyond the smoking stage and you see white ash in the skillet bottom, at least 10 minutes (the skillet can not be too hot for this dish).
Meanwhile, pour 2 tablespoons melted butter in each of the 6 small ramekins; set aside but keep warm in oven at 250°.

title: special lamb roast
directions: You will also need cheesecloth.

title: sheer heaven
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Place cherries, sugar and liquid in saucepan and bring to boil.
Boil a few minutes.
Pour over cherry jello.
Add Coke and when it gets cool, add pineapple and nuts.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: quick ham croquettes
directions: Melt Spry in saucepan.
Add flour, salt, pepper, mustard and onion in juice and blend.
Add milk and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add ham and blend.
Spread mixture in an 8 x 8-inch pan and chill until stiff.
Then cut into 8 triangles by cutting mixture twice from corner to corner, then twice more through center from side to side.

title: swiss chicken quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In medium bowl, toss cheese with flour and bouillon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Brown bacon (separately). Mix all ingredients in either slow cooker all day or large baking dish at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (uncovered).

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions; cook until tender, but not brown.
Add next 7 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook chicken and broccoli until done. Allow broccoli to cool.
Debone chicken; break into large pieces. Arrange broccoli in bottom of large greased casserole dish. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Place chicken on top, then pour on sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan and paprika.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, dice and set aside.
Blend milk, sugar, vinegar, 1 egg, butter, cornstarch, salt, celery seed and mustard; cook on low heat until thick.
To this add mayonnaise, onion, celery, parsley and diced hard-boiled eggs.
Add diced potatoes and mix well.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: pork chops with basil
directions: Mix flour and garlic salt and dredge pork chops.
Brown in skillet.
Put in bake pan.
Sprinkle with paprika and basil.
Add beef bouillon.
Cover tightly.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: In baking dish spread asparagus over bottom, cover with mushroom soup and eggs.
Then add crackers, top with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until bubbly around edge and cheese is melted (about 15 minutes).
Serves approximately 12 to 16.
Half recipe for smaller group.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Bake in greased and floured cookie sheet.
Let cool.
In large bowl, mix pudding and milk. Add cream cheese; mix well. Drain pineapple and add to cream cheese/pudding mix.
Spread over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle with cherries and nuts.

title: hash brown potato hot dish
directions: Mix all
together.
Pour
in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top as you take out of oven.

title: chicken foldovers
directions: Mix margarine, flour and cream cheese.
Chill.
Roll and cut with biscuit cutter into rounds.
Combine chicken and soup to make filling.
With fingertips, gather just enough filling for one round of dough.
Place on round and fold in half.
Seal edges.
Prick top with fork.
Sprinkle with paprika for color and flavor.
Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Makes 65 to 70 foldovers.

title: chili quiche appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan. Sprinkle chilies and cheese in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over cheese and chilies.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pear congealed salad
directions: Mix box lime jello with softened cream cheese.
Heat juice from the can of pears and pour into mixture.
Whip sliced pears and cream into mixture and refrigerate.

title: baked fresh asparagus
directions: Wash, drain and break off tough ends of asparagus spears. Arrange in 1 layer in baking pan if possible.
(I use a jelly roll pan.)

title: moon balls
directions: Mix dry milk, honey and peanut butter together until well blended.
Chill.
Form into balls the size of marbles and roll in cereal.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: delicious cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour in milk, egg and butter.
Mix well. Bake in greased pan in a 425° oven for approximately 20 minutes.

title: meatball shepherds pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, shape into meatballs, brown.
Remove and brown onions in drippings, blend in flour and undrained mushrooms.
Add meatballs, tomatoes, bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add peas and carrots, add oregano, season to taste.
Put in shallow baking dish, spread potatoes on top.
Brown under broiler.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt and sugar gradually. Fold in vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoonful.
Heat oven to 350°.
Put cookies in oven. Turn off heat.
Let cookies stay in oven overnight without opening door.

title: hershey syrup cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, margarine and syrup.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Peel and slice thin cucumbers.
Place layer at a time in bowl. Lightly salt between layers.
Let stand about 1 hour.
Then drain off juice.
Mix ingredients with cucumbers.
Use more if needed. Can also add tomatoes and onions with this.
Good for any lettuce too.
Mix to desired taste.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all together, except hot dogs.
Dip dog in batter and deep fry.

title: crab casserole
directions: Soak French bread in water (squeeze out water) and mix with crabmeat.
Saute chopped ingredients in margarine.
Add beaten eggs to seasoning and add crab mixture, parsley and onion tops and salt and pepper to taste.

title: crabby mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss crabmeat with lemon juice in medium bowl. Add all ingredients except mushrooms and Parmesan and mix well. Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Rinse baking sheet lightly with water, shaking off excess. Arrange mushrooms on sheet.
Cover with foil and bake 12 to 15 minutes. Remove foil and continue baking until tips are golden, about 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 24.

title: zingy hot pepper relish(boost the flavor of hamburgers with this peppy condiment.)
directions: Seed the peppers and mince. Chop the tomato.
Combine peppers, tomato, lemon juice, onion, oil and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Refrigerate until needed.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Spread in shallow pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Butter bottom of casserole.
Make a layer of crumbs, asparagus, nuts, soup and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Fry in butter.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll dinner rolls thin.
Bake until light brown at 350°. Cool.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix with salad dressing and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread on top of rolls.
Chop vegetables fine. Sprinkle on top.
Follow with cheese.

title: chex barbecue snack mix
directions: Stir together cereals, pretzels, crackers and peanuts in microwavable bowl; set aside. Stir together remaining ingredients until blended. Pour over cereal mixture in bowl, stirring until evenly coated. Microwave, uncovered, on High 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes. Spread on aluminum foil or paper towels to cool. Store in airtight container. Makes 7 1/2 cups snack.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put hamburg into 9 x 11-inch pan; salt and pepper to taste. Slice onion on top.
Sprinkle peas over.
Pour soup over.
Spread cheese, then Tater Tots.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until very little lumps or until smooth.
Mix butter and crumbs together.
Line dish with crumbs. Pour half of cream cheese mixture over crumbs.
Pour cherries on top of cream cheese mixture.
Pour rest of cream cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle with crumbs on top.

title: corn fritters
directions: Cut corn quite fine from cob.
Add flour, egg, milk and seasoning.
Cook like batter cakes, using enough fat to make fritters turn or drop into deep fat and fry like doughnuts.
Serve around a platter of fried chicken or other meat.

title: bev's awesome breakfast casserole
directions: Place croutons on bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan.
Brown and drain sausage and sprinkle over layer of croutons.
Pour cheese over sausage.
Mix the eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over the cheese.
Cover and refrigerate eight hours or overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes, until eggs are set.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Drain peach slices and place in a 9 x 13-inch Pam sprayed baking dish. Spread margarine on top of peach slices.
Mix flour and sugar well, then add juice from peaches and stir well.
Pour over peaches and bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.
Do not let it get dry. Serve with butter or ice cream on top of cobbler.

title: pear honey
directions: Wash, pare and core the pears; slice before measuring.
Put through a food chopper, using the fine blade.
Combine pears and pineapple.
Add rind and juice.
Add sugar and cook over slow heat, stirring frequently.
Cook 20 minutes.
Pour into jars to within 1/4 of top.
Put on caps.
Screw bands firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Yields 8 half pints.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice in a glass mixing bowl.
