Pour mixture into 9-inch graham cracker pie shell. Let sit in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Spoon cherry pie filling on top of mixture.
Refrigerate overnight, if possible.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: good pie crust
directions: Mix the flour and salt.
Mix 1/4 cup water to 1/3 cup of the flour mixture.
To remaining flour, add 2/3 cup shortening and mix well.
Add the flour paste mixture.
Let stand awhile and roll. Makes 2 crusts.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini according to directions.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: low sugar chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13 inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix milk with vanilla pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over the graham crackers.
Add a second layer of crackers.
Pour remaining pudding mixture over crackers and then add a third layer of graham crackers.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs in half.
Brown on all sides in frying pan.
Set aside. In small dish, add flour to mustard to make a paste. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Place ribs in baking dish. Pour sauce mixture over ribs.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Remove cover.
Bake 1 hour longer. Baste every 15 to 20 minutes, until done.

title: hard boiled eggs
directions: Place the desired number of large eggs in a single layer in a saucepan.
Add enough water to cover one inch above the eggs. Bring water just to a boil.
Remove pan from heat, cover and let eggs stand 15 minutes.
Carefully drain eggs into a colander and immediately run cold water over them, (or place them in ice water until completely cooled).

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars together in a bowl. Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together. Stir in M&M's. Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Melt 1 stick butter, 1 cup flour and nuts.
Spread in a 10 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until starts to brown, at 350°.

title: low calorie hot dish
directions: Chop cabbage in large pieces.
Place in bottom of greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Pour off fat and stir in raw rice.
Place meat mixture on top of cabbage and cover with soup and water.
Bake, covered, in a preheated 350° oven for at least 1 hour.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Mix all ingredients well. Pour in unbaked pie crust until brown. It may take an hour or longer.

title: sausage wedges
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Crumble and brown sausage.
Drain and sprinkle sausage over bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle sausage with cheese.
In small bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in salsa.
Pour egg mixture over cheese and sausage.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with sour cream and additional salsa.
Makes 12 appetizer servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Beat in mashed bananas.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and 1/2 cup warm water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients with yeast and water; let stand about 2 hours.
Then make your rolls.
Bake in hot oven, about 425°, for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients and coat potatoes well.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes on one side; turn and bake 30 minutes more until golden brown.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add milk until mixture is very soft.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: new potato antipasto
directions: Cook potatoes, covered, in a large saucepan in boiling lightly salted water for about 20 minutes or until tender.
Add carrots to potatoes during last 3 minutes of cooking.
Drain; cool slightly. Quarter potatoes.
In a plastic bag set in a large bowl, combine potatoes, carrots, broccoli and olives; set aside.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and onions, celery and pepper.
Drain as much grease off as possible.
Add Ragu, mushrooms, salt, pepper, marjoram, oregano and garlic to the meat mixture and simmer for about 2 hours.
Mix cooked spaghetti with sauce and top with 8 ounces of grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup Colby cheese; mix well.
Turn into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: roast beef, onion and au jus gravy
directions: Mix your gravy in a saucepan; slice your onion in slices longwise.
Put them in gravy along with your roast.
Leave it on simmer, uncovered, for about 45 minutes or until the onions are tender.
Serve on sub or hoagies with a dipping bowl of the gravy and dip your sandwich as you eat it.
Very good.
You can do it with a pot roast the same way.

title: italian creme cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat butter and shortening until combined.
Add sugar; beat on medium speed until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat well.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder and baking soda; add to egg yolk mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating just until combined after each addition.
Stir in coconut and pecans.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or glass dish.
Place slightly cooked broccoli in pan.
Lay chicken in between.
Pour soup and water over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes.
The last 10 minutes add French fried onions.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: basil chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in slow cooker. Sprinkle with pepper and basil.	Spread soup on top of chicken. Arrange slices of green pepper and onion on top of soup. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: apple crunch
directions: Slice apples into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and margarine.
When mixed, add egg.
Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm, not hot, with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding and sugar together.
Add oil and water; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each addition. Add sour cream and chips.
Bake in greased Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 1 hour before removing.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Line jelly roll pan with wax paper and grease lightly.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove roll onto towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar. Remove waxed paper while roll is still hot.
Roll loosely in towel and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: ann's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening well.
Beat in the egg.
Add vanilla, peanut butter, bran flakes and quick oats.
Add flour last that has been sifted with the baking powder and soda.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° approximately 10 minutes.

title: baked stuffed lobster
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook lobsters in boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Remove and let cool.
Saute peeled shrimp in butter.
Add cooked meat from 1 pound lobster, crab and scallops and heat through.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Add vanilla. Add dry ingredients and stir.
Roll out onto a floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters. Bake in a preheated 375° oven until slightly browned.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients until tender, 15 to 20 minutes; drain.
Combine soup with sour cream.
Mix with drained vegetables; set aside.
Melt margarine; mix with dressing mix. Layer 1/2 crumb mixture in baking dish.
Pour creamed vegetables over crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and chicken broth.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In casserole, layer 1/2 chicken, 1/2 tortilla chips, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat!
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix together. Best if stands overnight. Spread mixture on bottom of large baking sheet or large cake plate. Put layers: lettuce, onions, hamburger, cheese, tomatoes, olives and boiled eggs. Serve with chips.

title: salinas potato topper
directions: In saucepan over medium heat melt margarine.
Add broccoli; cook and stir until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in yogurt and Mozzarella.
To serve, spoon onto baked potato halves and sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 10 servings.

title: microwave denver sandwiches
directions: Combine green pepper, onion and butter in small mixing bowl. Microwave at High 1 to 2 1/2 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in eggs, chopped ham, milk and seasonings.
Pour into two small saucers.
Microwave at High 2 to 5 minutes or until eggs are almost set, pushing cooked portions toward center of dish and rotating saucers once or twice during cooking.
Serve open-face or as sandwiches with bread or toast.
Serves 4.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Wash and take out any bad spots.
Put tomatoes through Squeezo.
Cook juice until it boils. Strain the juice and add salt and sugar in quart jar. Process for 10 minutes.

title: meatless dressing
directions: Melt oleo in large pan.
Add celery, onion and water.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown.

title: worlds best sugar cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl with mixer at medium speed, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time until light and fluffy. Add oil, vanilla and lemon peel.
In another large bowl, combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Gradually add the dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Heat until well blended.
Cover and chill dough for several hours.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Divide dough into thirds.
Form heaping teaspoon of dough into a ball.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten dough to a 2-inch diameter with the bottom of a glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand on cookie sheet for 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: beet jelly
directions: Peel and cut up enough beets to use 6 to 7 cups of water to boil.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
Save juice.
Bring juice, Kool-Aid and Sure-Jell to a rolling boil. Add sugar.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Put jelly in glasses and seal or freeze.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage.
Add milk and flour to make a gravy.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with uncooked biscuits.
Add gravy/sausage mixture over biscuits.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar and flour.
Gradually add oil.
Take out one cup of this mixture.
Add to this cup the cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside for the topping.
Add to remaining mixture in your mixer bowl the buttermilk, salt, baking soda and eggs.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put on topping. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: skillet macaroni & spam
directions: Cook meat in large skillet until browned slightly.
Remove from skillet and add macaroni, onion and green pepper.
Cook in meat fat until macaroni is yellow (do not need a lot of fat). Return meat to skillet, along with tomato sauce, salt and papper, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until macaroni is cooked to suit your taste.
Variation:
Add 1 can whole kernel corn.

title: peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan or double boiler melt peanut butter chips, 1 cup Eagle Brand and 2 tablespoons butter; stir occasionally. Remove from heat; stir in peanuts.
Spread mixture into wax paper or foil lined 8-inch square pan.

title: fluffy tapioca cream
directions: Beat the egg white until foamy.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar, beating constantly, until the meringue will stand in soft peaks. Set aside.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, add onion while browning.
Drain and return to skillet.
Add tomato sauce, paste and mushrooms; stir.
Add a dash of chili powder.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, garlic and oregano.
Cover and simmer on low heat 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over spaghetti.
Serves 4 to 5 depending on appetites.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain and rinse.
In a small saucepan, melt butter, then add flour, salt and pepper.
Let it come to a boil.
Cook until mixture forms a paste.
Add soup (dry), water and whipping cream.
Bring to a boil again and set aside.

title: orange delight(weight watchers)
directions: Mix dry Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Add drained fruit and fold in topping.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: icing for cake
directions: Mix flour with milk and cook until thick.
Set aside to cool. Mix solid shortening, butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Mix with cool flour mixture until fluffy.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and mix together with onion, cheese and mayonnaise. Top with cracker crumbs.
Melt butter and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes.
Can mash potatoes (optional).
Add all ingredients to the cooked potatoes.

title: shell roni salad
directions: Cook shell noodles until done, drain and pour in large bowl. Add tuna, peas, onion, cheese and tomatoes.
In separate bowl, mix Miracle Whip, sugar, salt and pepper, and milk to smooth it.
Add these ingredients to taste.
Should be a little sweet.
Pour over other ingredients until creamy.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil macaroni as package directs.
Mix cream of mushroom and tuna in casserole dish.
Mix macaroni and soup and tuna together. Add peas in casserole dish. Warm in 350° (preheated) oven for 15 minutes.
Add crumbled crackers to top and top with cheese.
Melt cheese and serve.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water (use pineapple juice if desired).
Add cranberries.
Stir until dissolved.
Add raspberry sherbet.
Mix well.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Frost with Dream Whip.

title: microwave white sauce
directions: Melt margarine
in a 1 quart glass measuring pitcher in a microwave oven
(about
seconds on High).
Add flour and blend to
a
smooth
paste.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly. Cook
in
microwave
uncovered
4 minutes at High or until thickened;
stir
vigorously after 2 minutes, then every 30 seconds.
Stir in salt.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti 4 minutes; drain, then combine all ingredients and bake uncovered 45 minutes in 350°
oven.

title: hot, hearty golden puff
directions: Place half of the crackers in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Cover with Velveeta slices and onions.
Top with remaining crackers.
Combine milk, eggs and seasonings.
Pour over crackers. Let stand 1 hour and bake in a slow oven at 325° for 40 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crunchy sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; set aside.
Brown sausage and ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Combine rice and meat mixture; add all other ingredients except almonds, and mix thoroughly.
Spoon into ungreased 2 or 3 quart casserole; sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add softened cream cheese, mayonnaise, salt, cayenne pepper and horseradish.
Blend until smooth. Add lemon juice. Chill until slightly thick. Fold in cucumber and onion. Turn into 6 (1/2 cup) salad molds and chill. Unmold and garnish with cherry tomatoes.
A nice summer molded salad.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fudge custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add melted butter, egg yolks and milk to the mixture.
Put into unbaked shell.
Cook at 325° or 350° until set.

title: chicken skillet
directions: Spray large skillet with cooking spray.
Add chicken cubes, cook on medium-high for 5 minutes or until cooked through; stirring occasionally.
Add milk, water and shells; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium low; cover.
Simmer 15 minutes or until shells are tender stirring occasionally.
Add cheese sauce; stir until well blended.

title: creamy lemon bars
directions: Mix crumbs, 1/4 cup of the sugar and margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press mixture onto bottom of pan.
Beat cream cheese, remaining sugar and 2 tablespoons of the milk until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Pour remaining milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours until set or overnight.
Garnish with additional whipped topping before serving, if desired.
Makes 18 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake by package directions and spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven until cake tests done.
Remove and punch holes over the cake with toothpick.
While cake bakes, mix together pineapple and sugar, heat until sugar dissolves.
Spoon over cake.
Make up vanilla pudding mix.
When it thickens, spoon over cake.
Chill.
Spread cake with whipped topping.
Sprinkle coconut over top and refrigerate.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken breasts until tender. Remove bones and skin.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice. Place layer of chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with broccoli and pour mixture over top.
Cover with cheese and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: green and gold squash
directions: Wash and thinly slice squash.
Bring 1/2 inch of water to a boil in a wide saute pan with salt and shallots.
Add squash; cover pan and steam for 2 to 3 minutes or until tender.
Pour off water and toss squash with butter and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: mass tort feasor chili
directions: Brown the ground beef, add the salsa and simmer. Gradually add beef/salsa mixture into a pot of tomatoes. Stir in some chili powder and cinnamon, then draw something (like the letter R or the letter G) on top with the chocolate syrup and mix it in. Add the remainder of the beef/salsa, more chili powder and cinnamon, and another chocolate drawing. (If you do it in three stages, you could use the letters U, S and T or perhaps L, A and W.)

title: sugared crullers(makes 24 crullers)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat 1 cup flour into cooled milk.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and salt. Beat well.
Add the milk-flour combination and the yeast.
Gradually add 3 1/2 cups of flour until it forms a soft, not stiff dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Turn out on floured pastry cloth.
Press into 8 x 16-inch rectangle.
Cut in strips 2/3-inch wide by 8-inch.
Makes 24.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick. Cool.
It thickens as it cools.
Add sliced, partially thawed 16 ounce package unsweetened frozen strawberries. Pour into baked deep dish pie crust. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: *Applesauce or squash can be substituted for the pumpkin.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool.
Tear chicken into several pieces.
Add cream of chicken, cream of celery soup and Veg-All to chicken in casserole dish (salt and pepper to taste).
Mix egg, flour, milk and mayonnaise in bowl.
Pour onto casserole mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage stew
directions: Cut sausage in 1/2 pieces.
Brown in pot with oil and water. Takes approx. 25 mins.
After browned, add potatoes, onion, crushed tomatoes, cheese and another cup of water to simmer.
Add vegetables and cook till tender.

title: pepper jelly
directions: In saucepan, boil chopped peppers, vinegar, sugar and salt for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the Certo, bring to a boil, then add red or green food coloring.
Pour into jars.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green grape salad
directions: Cook butter, flour and milk until thick.
Pour over fruit, pecans and marshmallows.
Chill.

title: mmmpossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Cook and stir beef and onion in a 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper; spread in plate.
Combine Bisquick, milk and eggs with a wire whisk or handbeater until almost smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until a knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Garnish with lettuce. Serves 8.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into baking dish.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Combine the cherries, pineapple, dates, raisins and pecans. Pour 1/2 cup flour over all this and set aside.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Let cool, then add crushed pineapple with juice.
Stir in nuts and cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.
Cut into slices when jelled.

title: party bread("what do you do with a kumquat?")
directions: Put kumquats in a heavy pan with the sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and boil 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add beaten eggs and
oil. Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder, soda and spices. Stir in nuts.
Stir gently into kumquat mixture.
Cut a piece of wax paper to bottom of each of 2 loaf pans.
Grease and add batter.
Bake in a 350° oven until done, about 45 minutes.

title: roast beef and horseradish spirals
directions: In medium bowl combine cream cheese, horseradish, mustard, salt and pepper.
On a work surface, overlap 2 slices of roast beef to form a rectangle, about 8 x 4-inches.
Spread about 2 tablespoons of horseradish mixture over beef.
Beginning with long side, roll tightly.
Cover in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
To serve, slice crosswise on the diagonal.

title: betty's fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together flour, 2 cups of sugar, eggs and fruit cocktail. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: basic pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl of food processor fitted with steel blade. Pulse 2 or 3 times just to aerate. Add the shortening. Pulse rapidly until the mixture resembles coarse meal. Stop the processor. Add the water, starting with 2 tablespoons and adding more as needed until mixture forms a ball.
Form the dough into a disk about 4 or 5 inches in diameter. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: After boiling chicken, remove and set aside.
Add carrots, celery, peas and onion to broth.
Add bouillon cubes.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add seasoning, chicken and noodles; continue cooking until noodles are done.
More water may be added along with additional bouillon cubes, if desired.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened. Refrigerate.

title: brownie fudge pie
directions: Mix together eggs, flour, cocoa, butter, sugar, vanilla and pecans and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: mini peanut butter cups
directions: In a large bowl, beat first 4 ingredients with mixer on medium speed until combined. Add the egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well. Combine flour and baking soda. Add to egg mixture, beating well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Roll in the 1/4 cup sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven. Immediately press half of a peanut butter cup, cut side down, into each cookie, about 1/2-inch from bottom edge. Cool for 1 minute. Transfer cookies to rack. Cool.
tags: bite size chocolate covered peanut butter

title: fettucine with mussels
directions: Heat the wine in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat to boiling.
Add the mussels, cover the pan and cook until the shells open, about 5 minutes.
Remove the mussels from the shells and set aside.
Discard the shells.
Strain the cooking liquid and reserve.

title: arroz espanola(spanish rice)
directions: Melt bacon drippings in large skillet. Add rice and brown. When the rice is a golden brown, reduce heat and add onion, bell pepper, tomatoes, garlic and pepper. Mix well and add 1 1/2 cups of warm water or enough to just cover rice. Add salt. Cover and let simmer until almost dry. Add remaining water, cold a little at a time, cooking over low heat until fluffy. This is the secret to fluffy rice.

title: aunt sophie's smurcruse
directions: Work flour and butter together with pastry cutter.
Moisten with cream.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick and cut into 1/2 x 2 to 3-inch strips.
Make small slits along one side and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in hot oven at 375° to 400° for 20 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix meat with bread that has been soaked in milk, wrung dry and broken into small bits.
Add milk and eggs.
Saute onions in oil until tender.
Add with seasoning to meat mixture.
Stir in cheese.
Form into small balls and roll in flour.
Saute in oil in which onions were sauteed.
Fry until slightly browned and drop in Oregon Sauce.
Cook 1/2 hour
or until done.

title: carrot croquettes
directions: Mix together and form patties.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, if unsalted crackers are used, add 1/2 teaspoon salt.

title: microwave italian beef casserole
directions: Place ground
beef in shallow 3 quart microproof casserole; break up with fork.
Cook on High 5 to 7 minutes; drain. Add remaining
ingredients,
except
cheese; mix well.	Cover. Cook on High 9
minutes.
Stir;
cover.
Cook on High 12 to 14 minutes or until
noodles
are cooked.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: grape cooler
directions: Fill juice glasses 3/4 full of grape juice; add a small scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: breakfast before(6 servings)
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard together.
Pour egg mixture over sausage, bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Delicious served with fruit cup.

title: vegetable pilav(rice cooked with vegetables)
directions: Grind garlic and ginger into a paste.
In a saucepan, heat the butter over medium heat and saute the onion, cinnamon, cloves, bay leaves, mint and hot green peppers.
When onion turns light brown, add 4 cups of water.
When the mixture boils, add rice and salt. When rice is half cooked, add the vegetables and mix it well for 1 minute.
Then pour the mixture in a baking tray and bake it in a preheated oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Saute cashews in one tablespoon of butter in a frying pan over medium heat until golden brown and mix it with vegetable rice.
Serve it hot.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice; add sugar, egg yolks and vanilla, then add butter and cream until soupy.
Pour into Corning Ware skillet.
Beat egg whites, then add vanilla and slowly add 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour on top of pudding mixture and cook at 350° until egg whites are golden brown.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Place ice cream on serving plate.
Pipe frozen whipped topping over ice cream in a pretty design.
Place cherry pie filling on top.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars, peanut butter and eggs.
Blend well. Mix remaining ingredients and add to peanut butter mixture.
Drop and bake or shape in rolls, chill and slice to bake.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in fourths.
Shake in sugar and cinnamon mixture and put in greased Bundt or angel cake pan.
Pour leftover sugar mixture on top.
Heat margarine and brown sugar to boiling. Let boil about 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over rolls in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, crushed berries and cornstarch until thick. Stir in jello.
Cool.
Line bottom of pie shell with softened cheese.
Place whole berries on cheese.
Pour cooled mixture on top of berries.
Chill. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: benedictine spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: coconut pie(three minute pie)
directions: Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: spanish peanuts & green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least two hours before serving.
Serves 8.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients (save enough cheese to sprinkle over top). Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil zucchini and onion, about 5 minutes.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Mix margarine and dressing.
Layer in casserole dish, dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chili con carne
directions: Wash beans, cover with water. Cook until tender. In skillet, heat oil and saute beef, onion and garlic powder till brown. Drain grease. Add all ingredients to pinto beans. Simmer 2 hours. Serves 8-10.

title: vegetable crescent snack
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles; place crosswise on large cookie sheet.
Press perforations firmly to seal.
Bake 10 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
In small bowl, combine cream cheese, dip mix and mayonnaise.
Spread evenly on crescent strips.
Cut into finger-size pieces (1 x 2-inch).
Top with vegetable pieces.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal coconut crisp cookies
directions: *I cut the sugars to 3/4 cup each.

title: norwegian cheese crisp
directions: In frying pan, add butter.
Melt on medium.
Place lefse in pan.
Add grated cheese. Cook until cheese is melted and lefse is crisp.

title: spicy shrimp aspic
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold tomato juice.
Simmer garlic and parsley in some of the juice.
Pour through strainer into rest of the juice. Cool and add other ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse in cool water.
Chop celery, onion, pimento, eggs, bell pepper, tomatoes and shrimp.
Mix all together.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Place cut up apples in pie plate.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix butter, flour and sugar in bowl; stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour and pat over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick pizza
directions: Blend together and spread in pan.
Top with topping.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cook
first
three
ingredients
in pan on top of stove until soft and sticky.
Arrange slices of pineapple in bottom of greased
pan.
Fill
pineapple
centers
with
pecans
and cherries. Pour caramel mixture on top of pineapple.
Cover all with yellow cake batter (follows).

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each egg. Stir in sour cream. Blend well. Combine soda and flour together. Add flour to the sour cream mixture. Beat at lowest speed until well mixed.
Beat in vanilla. Smooth batter into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Makes 24 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bite size cinnamon rolls
directions: Spread out the rolls into squares (try not to flatten too much). Spread with the melted margarine. Sprinkle with the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Roll up and cut into slices.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: bucks taters
directions: Peel potatoes if desired.
Slice each potato crosswise at 1/4-inch intervals, cutting to but not through, opposite side. Carefully insert onion slices into cuts.
Sprinkle each potato with seasoned salt and pepper; dot with 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Wrap each potato in aluminum foil.
Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: eggless applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and spices.
Add raisins, nuts and soda last.
Beat in flour.
Bake in a slow oven at 350° for 35 minutes. Ice when cool, or is very good uniced.

title: old fashioned chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar, brown sugar, Crisco and butter.
Add and beat eggs, salt, milk and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wild rice with mushrooms and almonds
directions: Put all ingredients except broth, in a heavy skillet and cook oven medium heat for about 20 minutes or until the almonds are slightly brown.
Stir often.
Heat oven to 325°.
When almonds are brown, add the chicken broth to the rice mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover tightly and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: john's special fish dish
directions: Combine soup and milk in a large saucepan; heat slowly, stirring constantly, to prevent burning.
As the mixture becomes hot, add the sliced cheese, again stirring to smooth out lumps. Add garlic, oregano, parsley flakes and sherry.
Add fish to mixture and stir to blend all ingredients.
Transfer this mixture to an ovenproof casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top to coat.
Sprinkle bread crumbs with melted butter and place casserole in broiler long enough to lightly brown the bread crumbs.
Remove and serve.
Can be also served over rice bed, toast, noodles or just plain.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil together until fluffy.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to the sugar mixture.
Drop by tablespoons on an ungreased cookie sheet, only 6 cookies to a sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Yields 70 cookies.

title: holiday wreaths and trees
directions: Melt butter/margarine and marshmallows together.
Blend in vanilla and food coloring.
Fold in corn flakes.
Form into wreaths and trees on wax paper.
Decorate with red hots.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Drain syrup from all fruits.
Turn fruit into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter, sugar and curry powder in a pan with juices.
Pour mixture over fruit.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: apple fritter rings
directions: Core and peel apples; cut into 1/2-inch thick rings and set aside.
In a mixing bowl, thoroughly stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.

title: mary's ham roll
directions: Mix cream cheese, garlic and chopped nuts until smooth. Spread on ham slice.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Place roll in refrigerator until firm.
Slice and serve with crackers.

title: wassail
directions: Combine juices in a large saucepan.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag; add to juice.
Simmer mixture over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Add bourbon, if desired. Serve hot.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: melt in your mouth ham
directions: Place ham on large piece of aluminum foil and place in large baking pan.
Trim all fat from ham.
Spread a layer of mustard over entire ham.
Follow with a heavy layer of brown sugar. Secure pineapple slices on ham with toothpicks.
Pack crushed pineapple around slices; secure cherries with toothpicks in center of pineapple slices.
Wrap up ham with foil.
Bake at 325° for 4 to 5 hours.
Bake every 1 hour or so.
Enjoy!!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add zucchini.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to zucchini mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cheese and crab appetizers
directions: In medium bowl, combine soup, green onion, pimento and hot sauce.
Fold in crab meat.
Spread soup mixture evenly over 12 muffin halves and place on baking sheets.
Broil 6-inches from heat for 5 to 6 minutes or until hot and lightly browned.
Quarter each muffin half for 48 appetizers or serve as 12 open-faced sandwiches.

title: mound bars
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and butter with fork.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; blend.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, juice and rind.
Mix well.
Add sour cream and sugar.
Chill layered fruit in a large bowl.
(Layer fruit so that the colors are pretty.)
Spoon cream cheese mixture over the top of the fruit.
Sprinkle with nuts and chill.

title: little goodies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set in shallow pan.
Fill pan to 1 inch with hot water.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together the pumpkin and eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to pumpkin and egg mixture. Add the butter, Carnation milk and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Yields three 9-inch pies.

title: layer cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks and beat thoroughly. Add sifted dry ingredients with milk and vanilla.
Beat well. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost with your favorite frosting.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix sour cream and sugar until sugar is no longer grainy. (This is very important.)
Add Cool Whip and stir coconut in well. Ice between layers, sides and top of cake.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and let stand in refrigerator 1 to 3 days for best taste.
This cake also freezes well.

title: easy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients well.
Add eggs and oil; stir to mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes, until center sinks.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Saute liver and onion for 20 minutes; cool.
Place liver mixture and eggs in blender, a little at a time.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Blend until smooth.
Remove and garnish with parsley.
Yields 1 pint.
